00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:16.017 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki]
 <i>"I always have a premonition</i>
 <i>of losing something."</i>

00:00:16.050 --> 00:00:17.517 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's what she told me.</i>

00:00:17.551 --> 00:00:24.558 position:27% line:89% align:start
[commuting crowd]

00:00:33.567 --> 00:00:35.502 position:33% line:89% align:start
[train horn]

00:00:35.535 --> 00:00:38.572 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I was just a middle school</i>
 <i>student at the time,</i>

00:00:38.605 --> 00:00:41.976 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>so there was no way that</i>
 <i>I could really understand</i>
 <i>what she was saying.</i>

00:00:42.576 --> 00:00:43.743 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>But still,</i>

00:00:43.777 --> 00:00:46.746 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>those words of hers strangely</i>
 <i>moved my heart.</i>

00:00:56.824 --> 00:00:59.593 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>It was before the war,</i>

00:00:59.626 --> 00:01:03.097 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>when the huge island called Ezo</i>
 <i>was still a foreign territory.</i>

00:01:05.632 --> 00:01:12.639 position:30% line:89% align:start
[jet overhead]

00:01:23.717 --> 00:01:24.919 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Amazing!

00:01:28.521 --> 00:01:30.157 position:33% line:89% align:start
An airplane!

00:01:40.801 --> 00:01:43.170 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>On that distant day,</i>

00:01:43.204 --> 00:01:45.772 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>beyond those clouds,</i>

00:01:45.806 --> 00:01:47.574 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I had a promised place</i>
 <i>with her.</i>

00:01:51.212 --> 00:01:52.479 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri]
"While you were suffering..."

00:01:53.814 --> 00:01:54.882 position:19% line:89% align:start
"...from severe fever,

00:01:54.916 --> 00:01:58.718 position:19% line:83% align:start
you asked me to get one
final bowl full of snow...

00:01:58.752 --> 00:02:02.522 position:10% line:83% align:start
that fell from the sky of the
world called the galaxy,

00:02:02.555 --> 00:02:06.027 position:10% line:89% align:start
the sun, the sky, and so on.

00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:08.930 position:16% line:83% align:start
The sleet has accumulated
so desolately...

00:02:08.963 --> 00:02:11.665 position:21% line:83% align:start
on the two pieces of
granite stone.

00:02:11.698 --> 00:02:14.802 position:13% line:83% align:start
Standing on them, unstable,
from this pine tree,

00:02:14.835 --> 00:02:19.173 position:21% line:77% align:start
and its shiny branch
that keeps pure, white snow
full of clear, cold drops."

00:02:19.206 --> 00:02:22.043 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>In those days,</i>
 <i>we admired two things</i> .

00:02:24.577 --> 00:02:26.113 position:10% line:83% align:start
[girl] How many minutes left?
[friend] We've still got time.

00:02:36.824 --> 00:02:37.925 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Heads up.

00:02:37.959 --> 00:02:39.693 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] That's hot! Thanks.

00:02:39.726 --> 00:02:41.929 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Hiroki, when are you
going to work next time?

00:02:41.963 --> 00:02:44.265 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Well, since I've got
club activities until tomorrow,

00:02:44.298 --> 00:02:45.799 position:16% line:89% align:start
maybe the day after that?

00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:46.867 position:19% line:89% align:start
How about you, Takuya?

00:02:46.901 --> 00:02:49.937 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Tomorrow's my last
training day, so...

00:02:49.971 --> 00:02:51.705 position:24% line:83% align:start
How's the day after
tomorrow sound?

00:02:51.738 --> 00:02:52.840 position:44% line:89% align:start
Okay.

00:02:52.873 --> 00:02:54.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
[train arriving]

00:02:58.879 --> 00:03:03.117 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>One of the two things that</i>
 <i>we admired was our classmate,</i>
 <i>Sayuri Sawatari.</i>

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:04.852 position:38% line:89% align:start
[clatter]

00:03:04.885 --> 00:03:06.720 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>And the other...</i>

00:03:06.753 --> 00:03:10.224 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>was that enormous tower</i>
 <i>that rose beyond the border...</i>

00:03:10.257 --> 00:03:12.592 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>on the other side</i>
 <i>of the Tsugaru Strait.</i>

00:03:20.835 --> 00:03:23.170 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>I was always looking</i>
 <i>up at that tower</i> .

00:03:26.173 --> 00:03:28.275 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I felt something</i>
 <i>very important to me</i>

00:03:28.309 --> 00:03:30.911 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>was waiting at that place.</i>

00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:36.017 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I almost longed for that tower.</i>

00:03:48.762 --> 00:03:50.031 position:41% line:89% align:start
[bang]

00:04:01.641 --> 00:04:02.977 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Someday...</i>

00:04:21.628 --> 00:04:23.264 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Someday...</i>

00:04:23.297 --> 00:04:26.801 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Someday I'm going to get there.</i>

00:04:32.907 --> 00:04:34.075 position:16% line:89% align:start
[girl] Senior Shirakawa!

00:04:35.976 --> 00:04:37.078 position:21% line:89% align:start
Catch you later, man.

00:04:37.111 --> 00:04:38.578 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yeah, sorry.

00:04:40.414 --> 00:04:44.251 position:19% line:83% align:start
Um, we know you seniors
are retiring today, so...

00:04:44.285 --> 00:04:47.054 position:27% line:83% align:start
There's something
we'd like to give you.

00:04:47.088 --> 00:04:48.189 position:16% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Go on, Kana!

00:04:48.222 --> 00:04:49.589 position:41% line:89% align:start
What?!

00:04:52.692 --> 00:04:53.928 position:44% line:89% align:start
Um...

00:04:53.961 --> 00:04:54.995 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kana] Here...

00:04:56.997 --> 00:04:59.266 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] And you turned her
down, as usual.

00:05:00.868 --> 00:05:02.136 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm...

00:05:05.239 --> 00:05:08.675 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Matsuura in year one,
huh? She's cute though.

00:05:08.708 --> 00:05:10.177 position:27% line:83% align:start
If you think so,
you go out with her.

00:05:10.211 --> 00:05:11.711 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] What?!

00:05:11.744 --> 00:05:13.380 position:16% line:89% align:start
If it was you, would you?

00:05:13.414 --> 00:05:15.916 position:16% line:89% align:start
What? No... Why would I?

00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:18.119 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] So, you have someone
else you like?

00:05:18.152 --> 00:05:20.354 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] What? W-Why?

00:05:20.387 --> 00:05:22.689 position:21% line:83% align:start
Well, it's true that
I think she's cute,

00:05:22.722 --> 00:05:24.191 position:19% line:83% align:start
but I don't really know
what you do

00:05:24.225 --> 00:05:26.093 position:30% line:83% align:start
when you go out
with someone...

00:05:26.127 --> 00:05:27.895 position:10% line:89% align:start
Not really. Know what I mean?

00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:33.000 position:27% line:83% align:start
It wasn't you she
confessed her love to.

00:05:33.033 --> 00:05:34.268 position:19% line:89% align:start
You asked me about it!

00:05:34.301 --> 00:05:37.004 position:33% line:89% align:start
[school bell]

00:05:46.914 --> 00:05:48.215 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Sayuri...</i>

00:06:08.068 --> 00:06:09.470 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hiroki!

00:06:09.503 --> 00:06:11.172 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sayuri.

00:06:11.205 --> 00:06:13.107 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] You're going home late.

00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:16.310 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Yeah, I was late
because I was practicing...

00:06:16.343 --> 00:06:19.013 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Violin?
[Sayuri] Yeah...

00:06:19.046 --> 00:06:20.314 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] You're not with Takuya?

00:06:21.748 --> 00:06:24.784 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah, I was also
doing club activities.

00:06:24.818 --> 00:06:26.187 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri]
I notice you sometimes practice

00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:27.988 position:16% line:89% align:start
your archery by yourself.

00:06:28.022 --> 00:06:31.192 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yeah well, I'm...
I'm not really that good yet.

00:06:31.225 --> 00:06:33.093 position:16% line:89% align:start
My mind wanders a lot...

00:06:38.165 --> 00:06:41.468 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Do you have any plans
during spring break?

00:06:41.502 --> 00:06:44.438 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah, I'm going to
be working with Takuya.

00:06:44.471 --> 00:06:47.074 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Work?
I'm jealous! Where?

00:06:47.107 --> 00:06:49.310 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] At a military factory
in Hamana.

00:06:49.343 --> 00:06:51.245 position:13% line:83% align:start
Working on guided missiles
and stuff.

00:06:52.980 --> 00:06:55.182 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] It's great that
you've got a job.

00:06:55.216 --> 00:06:57.384 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've only got my
club activities...

00:06:58.252 --> 00:06:59.353 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Really?

00:06:59.386 --> 00:07:01.055 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Yeah...

00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:16.837 position:13% line:83% align:start
[speaker] The next station
is Nakaoguni, Nakaoguni.

00:07:16.870 --> 00:07:19.139 position:13% line:77% align:start
[speaker] After Nakaoguni,
we'll stop at Oodaira.
[Sayuri] Oh, this is my stop.

00:07:20.140 --> 00:07:22.176 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] You know, yesterday,

00:07:22.209 --> 00:07:24.378 position:10% line:83% align:start
I had a dream I would go home
with you like this...

00:07:28.582 --> 00:07:29.883 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Bye-bye!

00:07:29.917 --> 00:07:31.018 position:19% line:89% align:start
See you next semester!

00:07:32.019 --> 00:07:33.254 position:41% line:89% align:start
Okay...

00:07:34.288 --> 00:07:35.456 position:33% line:89% align:start
[train horn]

00:08:05.619 --> 00:08:08.088 position:7% line:83% align:start
[radio] At the 11th Ministerial
Level Conference...

00:08:08.122 --> 00:08:09.423 position:7% line:89% align:start
between America and the Union,

00:08:09.456 --> 00:08:11.558 position:16% line:83% align:start
scheduled for three days
from the 12th,

00:08:11.592 --> 00:08:15.496 position:16% line:77% align:start
it appears that the focus
will be Japan's response to
the North-South problem,

00:08:15.529 --> 00:08:17.598 position:10% line:89% align:start
continuing to cause tension.

00:08:17.631 --> 00:08:20.167 position:5% line:83% align:start
The Union government shows their
deep concerns about...

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:22.002 position:5% line:89% align:start
the reinforcement of Misawa Base

00:08:22.036 --> 00:08:24.104 position:33% line:83% align:start
and the other
American facilities.

00:08:24.138 --> 00:08:26.607 position:24% line:77% align:start
On the other hand,
the American government
shows their uneasiness...

00:08:26.640 --> 00:08:27.941 position:5% line:89% align:start
towards the fact that the Union-

00:08:27.975 --> 00:08:29.310 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Hello!

00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:31.378 position:13% line:83% align:start
Cool! I'm just in time for
a tea break?

00:08:31.412 --> 00:08:33.013 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah, have a seat.

00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.048 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Okay.

00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:36.183 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] You're late, Hiroki.
[Hiroki] Sorry.

00:08:36.216 --> 00:08:38.118 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hiroki, I heard about it.

00:08:38.152 --> 00:08:41.088 position:10% line:83% align:start
So you guys went and stole a
Chukar from the MSDF, huh?

00:08:41.121 --> 00:08:43.023 position:19% line:77% align:start
[Takuya] Like I said...
That's not true!
[Hiroki] That's not true!

00:08:43.057 --> 00:08:44.291 position:24% line:89% align:start
We didn't steal it.

00:08:44.325 --> 00:08:45.959 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] We found it
in Amagamori!

00:08:47.027 --> 00:08:47.995 position:7% line:89% align:start
[worker b] So you did steal it.

00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:49.630 position:7% line:83% align:start
[worker a] Well, I guess it'll
be all right,

00:08:49.663 --> 00:08:52.299 position:5% line:83% align:start
since they fly drones in lots of
training these days.

00:08:52.333 --> 00:08:55.202 position:10% line:83% align:start
But just make sure they can't
trace it back to you guys.

00:08:55.235 --> 00:08:57.204 position:16% line:83% align:start
[worker b] That's right.
The Public Safety Commission

00:08:57.237 --> 00:09:00.341 position:30% line:83% align:start
already watches
this place, so...

00:09:00.374 --> 00:09:04.411 position:30% line:77% align:start
[door opening]
[Okabe] Let's stop saying things
that could smear my reputation!

00:09:04.445 --> 00:09:06.146 position:13% line:89% align:start
Now back to work, you guys!

00:09:06.180 --> 00:09:07.948 position:21% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Yes, Sir.

00:09:07.981 --> 00:09:10.050 position:30% line:77% align:start
See you later.
[Takuya] Yeah.
[Hiroki] See ya.

00:09:10.084 --> 00:09:13.153 position:13% line:77% align:start
I want you two kids to come
right to work tomorrow,
you got it?

00:09:13.187 --> 00:09:16.056 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll work you for more than what
those materials cost.

00:09:16.090 --> 00:09:17.191 position:27% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Okay.

00:09:17.224 --> 00:09:18.258 position:10% line:89% align:start
Well then, we're outta here.

00:09:19.159 --> 00:09:20.227 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Okay.

00:09:22.329 --> 00:09:25.299 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>There was a reason</i>
 <i>we started working</i> .

00:09:25.332 --> 00:09:27.601 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I heard that when Ezo was still</i>
 <i>called Hokkaido,</i>

00:09:27.634 --> 00:09:29.470 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>and was part of this country,</i>

00:09:29.503 --> 00:09:32.973 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>there was a plan to dig a tunnel</i>
 <i>underneath the Tsugaru Strait.</i>

00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:37.111 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>It ended up being interrupted</i>

00:09:37.144 --> 00:09:39.646 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>because of the North-South</i>
 <i>division,</i>

00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:41.982 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>but around this area in</i>
 <i>the mountains,</i>

00:09:42.015 --> 00:09:44.184 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>traces of its construction,</i>

00:09:44.218 --> 00:09:47.888 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>discontinued stations and</i>
 <i>rails, remained here and there.</i>

00:09:49.423 --> 00:09:52.626 position:27% line:77% align:start
 <i>In one of those</i>
 <i>discontinued stations</i>
 <i>on top of this mountain,</i>

00:09:52.659 --> 00:09:56.096 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>we'd been making something</i>
 <i>since last year.</i>

00:09:56.130 --> 00:09:58.132 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>The reason we worked at</i>
 <i>Emishi Plant,</i>

00:09:58.165 --> 00:10:00.968 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>a US subcontracted</i>
 <i>military factory,</i>

00:10:01.001 --> 00:10:04.138 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>was to earn money for the parts</i>
 <i>for what we were building.</i>

00:10:04.171 --> 00:10:06.106 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>That place that,</i>
 <i>even though we could see it</i>

00:10:06.140 --> 00:10:08.275 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>so close</i>
 <i>we could almost touch it,</i>

00:10:08.308 --> 00:10:10.544 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>we couldn't go.</i>

00:10:10.577 --> 00:10:13.680 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>We wanted to see with our own</i>
 <i>eyes that unknown island...</i>

00:10:13.714 --> 00:10:16.316 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>and the enormous Tower</i>
 <i>that rose there.</i>

00:10:16.350 --> 00:10:18.051 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>No matter what.</i>

00:10:22.689 --> 00:10:24.691 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Looks like a lot
of snow melted.

00:10:24.725 --> 00:10:26.627 position:16% line:89% align:start
I want to start up again.

00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:29.530 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah, if we don't
get any more.

00:10:29.563 --> 00:10:33.033 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Takuya]
At any rate, we'd better get the
rest of the materials we need.

00:10:33.066 --> 00:10:36.437 position:24% line:77% align:start
We still don't have
the outer nanonet or
the self-starting motor.

00:10:36.470 --> 00:10:39.039 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] The big thing's the
superconducting motor.

00:10:39.072 --> 00:10:42.109 position:19% line:83% align:start
And we'll need kerosene
too, man...

00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:45.179 position:10% line:83% align:start
We might not earn enough with
just the work from tomorrow.

00:10:45.212 --> 00:10:48.182 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki]
It'll work out, somehow. We have
summer break too, you know.

00:10:48.215 --> 00:10:51.351 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah, that's true.

00:10:51.385 --> 00:10:55.155 position:10% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>So we were planning</i>
 <i>to fly to that Tower</i>
 <i>beyond the border.</i> ..

00:10:55.189 --> 00:10:59.626 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>in this airplane that we named</i>
Bella Ciela.

00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:54.114 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] That same
dream again...

00:12:08.362 --> 00:12:09.596 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Sayuri.

00:12:11.532 --> 00:12:13.567 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Takuya...

00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:31.351 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] So you-
[Sayuri] Oh, uh-

00:12:31.385 --> 00:12:32.686 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Sorry.

00:12:32.719 --> 00:12:34.421 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] It's okay.

00:12:37.658 --> 00:12:38.692 position:10% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Hiroki said that-

00:12:43.463 --> 00:12:45.332 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggle]

00:12:45.365 --> 00:12:50.337 position:7% line:83% align:start
We haven't spent too much time
alone together, have we?

00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:51.738 position:27% line:89% align:start
You may be right.

00:12:53.307 --> 00:12:56.610 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] So, Takuya,
do you like physics?

00:12:56.643 --> 00:12:59.780 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Oh, this book?
Yeah, I'm interested in it.

00:12:59.814 --> 00:13:01.515 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] That's amazing.

00:13:01.548 --> 00:13:03.717 position:16% line:83% align:start
I was told my grandfather
was a physicist.

00:13:03.750 --> 00:13:06.520 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Really?
Well, that's certainly more

00:13:06.553 --> 00:13:08.455 position:30% line:83% align:start
amazing than my
interest in the subject.

00:13:08.488 --> 00:13:10.490 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Though,
I've never met him.

00:13:10.524 --> 00:13:12.159 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Because of the
North-South division?

00:13:12.192 --> 00:13:13.293 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Yeah...

00:13:13.327 --> 00:13:14.428 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] I see...

00:13:18.765 --> 00:13:22.603 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Hey, you guys are still
working, right? Is it fun?

00:13:22.636 --> 00:13:26.340 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Takuya]
I don't know. The factory's
owned by this scary old man.

00:13:26.373 --> 00:13:28.575 position:13% line:83% align:start
He works us pretty hard and
yells at us a lot.

00:13:28.609 --> 00:13:30.210 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Is he that scary?

00:13:30.243 --> 00:13:31.445 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] He's a demon.

00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:32.746 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Really?

00:13:32.779 --> 00:13:34.648 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] You wanna come
see the place?

00:13:34.681 --> 00:13:37.417 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Won't I be in
your way, though?

00:13:37.451 --> 00:13:39.686 position:5% line:89% align:start
No and Hiroki'd like to see you.

00:13:39.720 --> 00:13:41.889 position:19% line:89% align:start
Great! Then I'll come!

00:13:41.923 --> 00:13:43.624 position:10% line:83% align:start
[speaker] The train bound for
Kanita and Minmaya...

00:13:43.657 --> 00:13:45.759 position:13% line:89% align:start
is arriving at Platform 2.

00:13:45.792 --> 00:13:48.762 position:16% line:83% align:start
Please step back and wait
behind the white line.

00:13:50.364 --> 00:13:51.732 position:27% line:89% align:start
Um, hey, Takuya?

00:13:53.533 --> 00:13:56.403 position:16% line:83% align:start
This might sound strange,
so you promise not to laugh?

00:13:56.436 --> 00:13:59.239 position:10% line:89% align:start
What? Tell me, I won't laugh.

00:13:59.272 --> 00:14:00.875 position:16% line:89% align:start
Okay then, I'll tell you.

00:14:00.908 --> 00:14:02.810 position:27% line:89% align:start
[train arriving]

00:14:19.226 --> 00:14:20.928 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why did you do something
like that without asking?

00:14:20.962 --> 00:14:22.596 position:13% line:89% align:start
What was I supposed to do?

00:14:22.629 --> 00:14:25.565 position:7% line:83% align:start
The conversation was just going
in that direction.

00:14:34.909 --> 00:14:36.576 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] What do we do?

00:14:36.610 --> 00:14:38.946 position:21% line:83% align:start
Do we tell her about
flying to the Tower too?

00:14:38.980 --> 00:14:40.882 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] That wouldn't be
a good idea.

00:14:40.915 --> 00:14:42.083 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Right...

00:14:42.116 --> 00:14:44.584 position:7% line:83% align:start
So what do we say if she wants
to know where we're going?

00:14:48.990 --> 00:14:50.958 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey there...

00:14:50.992 --> 00:14:52.225 position:27% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Huh?!

00:15:03.938 --> 00:15:06.974 position:35% line:89% align:start
Uh, hello.

00:15:07.008 --> 00:15:08.810 position:21% line:89% align:start
Man, is it hot today-

00:15:08.843 --> 00:15:10.677 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hello, Sir. How are you?

00:15:10.711 --> 00:15:12.312 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hello there. Sorry.

00:15:12.345 --> 00:15:14.281 position:33% line:89% align:start
Well... uh...

00:15:14.314 --> 00:15:17.317 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] So the kids have told
me an awful lot about you.

00:15:18.452 --> 00:15:24.458 position:30% line:89% align:start
[jet overhead]

00:15:24.491 --> 00:15:25.827 position:33% line:89% align:start
Mr. Okabe...

00:15:26.493 --> 00:15:27.995 position:30% line:89% align:start
Was he single?

00:15:28.029 --> 00:15:30.865 position:24% line:83% align:start
Nah, I heard he was
divorced once.

00:15:30.898 --> 00:15:33.533 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki]
Somehow that makes sense.
[Okabe] Well thank you so much!

00:15:39.506 --> 00:15:41.909 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] I didn't know a place
like this existed!

00:15:41.943 --> 00:15:42.977 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's so big!

00:15:55.756 --> 00:15:58.492 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Amazing! An airplane?

00:15:58.525 --> 00:15:59.793 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:16:01.495 --> 00:16:03.797 position:21% line:83% align:start
Are you two building
this yourselves?

00:16:03.831 --> 00:16:04.999 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki]
Yeah. We've been working

00:16:05.032 --> 00:16:07.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
little by little since
the year two summer.

00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:09.569 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] We're working at the
factory to pay for parts.

00:16:09.603 --> 00:16:11.638 position:16% line:83% align:start
Mr. Okabe's been helping
us a lot.

00:16:11.671 --> 00:16:13.507 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Right?
[Hiroki] Mmhmm...

00:16:13.540 --> 00:16:15.709 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] It's still far from
being finished though.

00:16:15.742 --> 00:16:17.277 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] It's amazing...

00:16:19.013 --> 00:16:20.680 position:33% line:89% align:start
It really is!

00:16:23.483 --> 00:16:24.551 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Thanks...

00:16:49.110 --> 00:16:52.746 position:7% line:83% align:start
Hey, when is the airplane going
to be finished?

00:16:52.779 --> 00:16:54.347 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] We actually want
to complete it

00:16:54.381 --> 00:16:56.083 position:13% line:89% align:start
during the summer break...

00:16:56.117 --> 00:16:58.085 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] But we probably
can't do it.

00:16:58.119 --> 00:17:00.855 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Seems like it's gonna
take a lot more time.

00:17:00.888 --> 00:17:03.623 position:7% line:83% align:start
Our goal is to finish it before
the end of the year.

00:17:03.657 --> 00:17:04.892 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] I see...

00:17:04.926 --> 00:17:07.929 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, where are you going
in your plane?

00:17:09.831 --> 00:17:11.731 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] We're going to
that tower.

00:17:15.002 --> 00:17:17.337 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Tower? You mean the
Union Tower?

00:17:20.141 --> 00:17:21.341 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mmhmm...

00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:24.111 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] We think it'll take
about 40 minutes to fly there.

00:17:24.145 --> 00:17:26.948 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] The question is how
we cross the border,

00:17:26.981 --> 00:17:29.382 position:16% line:83% align:start
but we've got some ideas
about that, too.

00:17:29.416 --> 00:17:33.687 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Wow!
Hokkaido sounds great!

00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.122 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] You wanna go
with us, Sayuri?

00:17:35.156 --> 00:17:37.457 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] What? Is it okay?

00:17:37.490 --> 00:17:38.692 position:24% line:89% align:start
[in unison] Mmhmm!

00:17:38.725 --> 00:17:42.063 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Really? Yes, I'll go!
I wanna go!

00:17:42.096 --> 00:17:43.697 position:30% line:89% align:start
Wow! Thank you!

00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:45.867 position:24% line:83% align:start
But I don't know if
it'll be able to fly.

00:17:45.900 --> 00:17:48.002 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't worry! It'll fly!

00:17:48.035 --> 00:17:49.136 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Yeah!

00:17:49.170 --> 00:17:51.471 position:13% line:89% align:start
Okay, then it's a promise!

00:17:51.504 --> 00:17:52.706 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Yeah.

00:17:52.739 --> 00:17:54.608 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] It's a promise.

00:17:54.641 --> 00:17:55.742 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Okay!

00:18:03.117 --> 00:18:04.952 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>In those days,</i>

00:18:04.986 --> 00:18:08.622 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>I felt that time and place</i>
 <i>would continue on</i>
 <i>like that the rest of my life.</i>

00:18:08.655 --> 00:18:10.624 position:38% line:89% align:start
[thunder]

00:18:10.657 --> 00:18:13.627 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The Tower that was beyond</i>
 <i>the clouds that I admired,</i>

00:18:13.660 --> 00:18:16.529 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>became an important promised</i>
 <i>place to me.</i>

00:18:18.933 --> 00:18:21.802 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I think there was nothing for</i>
 <i>us to fear at that moment.</i>

00:18:24.038 --> 00:18:30.077 position:19% line:77% align:start
 <i>But the truth was that</i>
 <i>the world and history</i>
 <i>were changing all around us.</i>

00:18:30.111 --> 00:18:31.645 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>But in those days,</i>

00:18:31.678 --> 00:18:35.016 position:33% line:77% align:start
 <i>I felt only</i>
 <i>the smell of the night</i>
 <i>floating in the train,</i>

00:18:35.049 --> 00:18:37.118 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>the trust toward my friend,</i>

00:18:37.151 --> 00:18:39.987 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>and the hint of Sayuri</i>
 <i>that shook the air,</i>

00:18:40.021 --> 00:18:42.089 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>were everything in the world.</i>

00:18:51.564 --> 00:18:54.467 position:13% line:5% align:start
[TV] From late last night,
until before dawn this morning,

00:18:54.501 --> 00:18:56.203 position:24% line:5% align:start
in the buffer area
that lies between the

00:18:56.237 --> 00:18:59.673 position:24% line:5% align:start
42nd latitude line
and off the Tsugaru Strait,

00:18:59.706 --> 00:19:02.043 position:24% line:5% align:start
a small scale armed
conflict occurred between

00:19:02.076 --> 00:19:05.813 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>the US/Japanese military</i>
 <i>and the Union military.</i>

00:19:05.846 --> 00:19:07.348 position:21% line:89% align:start
Receiving this news,

00:19:07.381 --> 00:19:09.683 position:19% line:77% align:start
the Metropolitan Police
Department announced
that they will deploy 3300-

00:19:09.716 --> 00:19:12.186 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

00:19:12.219 --> 00:19:13.586 position:44% line:89% align:start
Okay.

00:19:16.857 --> 00:19:21.228 position:41% line:77% align:start
[Okabe]
Of course I'll sell you kerosene
or anything else if you pay.

00:19:21.262 --> 00:19:23.965 position:7% line:89% align:start
But jet fuel? That's expensive.

00:19:23.998 --> 00:19:26.566 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why don't you just use a
reciprocating engine,

00:19:26.599 --> 00:19:28.635 position:13% line:89% align:start
or a superconducting motor?

00:19:32.139 --> 00:19:33.573 position:27% line:89% align:start
You got the rest?

00:19:33.606 --> 00:19:34.708 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:19:34.741 --> 00:19:36.010 position:21% line:89% align:start
Then take care of it.

00:19:48.889 --> 00:19:53.127 position:27% line:77% align:start
Hey, why the hell
do you wanna take the trouble
of using jet engines?

00:19:53.160 --> 00:19:55.795 position:10% line:83% align:start
[in unison] 'Cause it's cool!
Is that the reason?

00:19:55.830 --> 00:19:56.864 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki]
Hold on a second,

00:19:56.897 --> 00:19:59.133 position:16% line:83% align:start
there were a lot of other
reasons, weren't there?

00:19:59.166 --> 00:20:01.135 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Let's see...
Oh, that one!

00:20:01.168 --> 00:20:02.602 position:16% line:83% align:start
[in unison] We were lucky
to find it!

00:20:02.635 --> 00:20:04.604 position:30% line:89% align:start
That's not it!

00:20:04.637 --> 00:20:05.605 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki]
What was it?

00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.975 position:16% line:83% align:start
Remember, the reason for
making it a dual engine?

00:20:08.009 --> 00:20:09.276 position:7% line:89% align:start
There was a good reason for it.

00:20:09.310 --> 00:20:10.610 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Oh, that was it!

00:20:10.643 --> 00:20:12.046 position:16% line:83% align:start
[in unison] We wanted it
to transform!

00:20:12.079 --> 00:20:13.247 position:21% line:89% align:start
[boys] That's not it!

00:20:15.149 --> 00:20:16.283 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] I don't care
what it is...

00:20:16.317 --> 00:20:20.888 position:13% line:83% align:start
Just don't die. It'll mean
nothing but trouble for me.

00:20:20.921 --> 00:20:23.290 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Okay, you kids be sure
to come right to work...

00:20:23.324 --> 00:20:25.692 position:21% line:83% align:start
every day when summer
break starts.

00:20:25.725 --> 00:20:26.760 position:33% line:89% align:start
[boys] Okay!

00:20:28.262 --> 00:20:29.629 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] So...

00:20:29.662 --> 00:20:31.098 position:7% line:89% align:start
You really want me to play it?

00:20:31.132 --> 00:20:33.566 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah, we'll come see
you after school.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:34.567 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door closing]

00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:39.706 position:13% line:83% align:start
Hey, I'm just telling you,
I'm not that good...

00:20:39.739 --> 00:20:40.808 position:33% line:89% align:start
Don't worry.

00:20:40.841 --> 00:20:42.709 position:19% line:83% align:start
I've never seen someone
play the violin in person.

00:20:42.742 --> 00:20:44.744 position:30% line:89% align:start
I want to hear.

00:20:44.778 --> 00:20:46.213 position:19% line:89% align:start
I want to hear it, too.

00:20:47.948 --> 00:20:49.817 position:16% line:89% align:start
I feel kind of nervous...

00:21:05.266 --> 00:21:12.306 position:44% line:89% align:start
[♪♪]

00:21:52.813 --> 00:21:54.982 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Nanonet doesn't
reflect radar, does it?

00:21:55.015 --> 00:21:57.218 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] But we're going to be
flying in the buffer area.

00:21:57.251 --> 00:22:00.988 position:16% line:83% align:start
Even if it has a nanonet
exterior, if we fly carelessly,

00:22:01.021 --> 00:22:04.291 position:10% line:83% align:start
the US military will spot us
before the Union does.

00:22:05.758 --> 00:22:07.128 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I guess we don't have
any other choice...

00:22:07.161 --> 00:22:09.662 position:10% line:83% align:start
but to fly as low as possible
and mix in the wave

00:22:09.696 --> 00:22:11.265 position:13% line:89% align:start
and the shape of the land.

00:22:11.298 --> 00:22:12.799 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] If we leave
early in the morning,

00:22:12.833 --> 00:22:14.802 position:30% line:83% align:start
we can hide in
the morning haze, too.

00:22:14.835 --> 00:22:16.270 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] We have a map of Ezo?

00:22:16.303 --> 00:22:17.538 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] This is the only
detailed one.

00:22:17.571 --> 00:22:20.841 position:7% line:83% align:start
We won't know the actual shape
of the land until we go there,

00:22:20.875 --> 00:22:23.344 position:10% line:83% align:start
so we'll have to measure the
altitude after landing.

00:22:23.377 --> 00:22:25.346 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] But isn't it the case
that so long as we land,

00:22:25.379 --> 00:22:28.015 position:16% line:83% align:start
the Union's radars won't
catch us?

00:22:28.048 --> 00:22:29.416 position:27% line:83% align:start
The <i>Bella Ciela's</i>
radar profile

00:22:29.450 --> 00:22:31.751 position:19% line:83% align:start
should be smaller than
a small bird, right?

00:22:31.784 --> 00:22:36.056 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Probably... Unless
we're really, really unlucky.

00:23:25.506 --> 00:23:31.345 position:30% line:89% align:start
[jet overhead]

00:23:37.351 --> 00:23:38.785 position:41% line:89% align:start
[boom]

00:23:45.259 --> 00:23:46.427 position:41% line:89% align:start
[crack]

00:24:05.512 --> 00:24:07.181 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Sayuri!

00:24:12.253 --> 00:24:13.420 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hang on!

00:24:18.392 --> 00:24:19.493 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's all right.

00:24:19.526 --> 00:24:21.328 position:13% line:89% align:start
I mean, it's not that far.

00:24:28.168 --> 00:24:30.904 position:13% line:89% align:start
We've had this before we...

00:24:35.309 --> 00:24:37.211 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I'm glad I made
it on time.

00:24:37.244 --> 00:24:38.778 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'll just-
[crack] [scream]

00:24:54.395 --> 00:24:56.363 position:30% line:89% align:start
You all right?

00:24:56.397 --> 00:24:57.498 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mmhmm...

00:24:57.531 --> 00:25:00.034 position:27% line:89% align:start
Sorry. Thank you.

00:25:01.935 --> 00:25:02.936 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Hey!

00:25:05.339 --> 00:25:06.807 position:27% line:89% align:start
That was awesome!

00:25:08.008 --> 00:25:09.310 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] What are you doing?!

00:25:09.343 --> 00:25:11.245 position:21% line:89% align:start
Knock it off, Hiroki!

00:25:11.278 --> 00:25:13.514 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Sorry, I just had to.

00:25:13.547 --> 00:25:15.949 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] What'd you say?!

00:25:15.983 --> 00:25:17.418 position:7% line:89% align:start
What'd you go and do that for?

00:25:17.451 --> 00:25:20.321 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Oh, come on,
don't be angry like that.

00:25:20.354 --> 00:25:22.189 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Oh,
I'm angry all right!

00:25:22.222 --> 00:25:23.924 position:30% line:89% align:start
Now stay there!

00:25:23.957 --> 00:25:26.060 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's go, Sayuri.

00:25:26.093 --> 00:25:27.194 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Takuya...

00:25:27.227 --> 00:25:29.129 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sayuri, say something to him!

00:25:29.163 --> 00:25:30.264 position:35% line:89% align:start
[giggling]

00:25:30.297 --> 00:25:31.899 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Sorry, Takuya.

00:25:31.932 --> 00:25:35.202 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Hiroki's stupid.
Forget about him and let's go.

00:25:35.235 --> 00:25:36.837 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Hey, Takuya...

00:25:50.584 --> 00:25:52.419 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] I was having
a dream earlier.

00:25:52.453 --> 00:25:54.955 position:24% line:89% align:start
Just for a second.

00:25:54.988 --> 00:25:57.191 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] A dream?
What kind of dream?

00:25:57.224 --> 00:26:01.128 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] Hmm...
I forgot, actually.

00:26:01.161 --> 00:26:04.231 position:13% line:83% align:start
But it was probably a dream
about that Tower.

00:26:04.264 --> 00:26:06.367 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] It's a pretty amazing
view, isn't it?

00:26:06.400 --> 00:26:09.169 position:16% line:89% align:start
The Union is incredible.

00:26:09.203 --> 00:26:13.407 position:21% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki] I feel like
the top of the Tower could
even lead to some other world.

00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:31.658 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] The sun...

00:26:31.692 --> 00:26:35.329 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's setting so
slowly, isn't it?

00:26:35.362 --> 00:26:37.564 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>That was a really</i>
 <i>special summer..</i> .

00:26:39.700 --> 00:26:41.668 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>But the world surrounding</i>
 <i>me would betray me</i>

00:26:41.702 --> 00:26:44.304 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>so many times</i>
 <i>from that point on.</i>

00:26:47.107 --> 00:26:50.444 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I haven't seen Sayuri for</i>
 <i>three years since that day...</i>

00:27:22.142 --> 00:27:26.213 position:35% line:89% align:start
[footsteps]

00:27:41.161 --> 00:27:43.030 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] We have some
visitors, gentlemen.

00:27:43.063 --> 00:27:44.598 position:13% line:89% align:start
But don't worry about them.

00:27:44.631 --> 00:27:47.568 position:21% line:83% align:start
1st Phase completed.
Let's proceed to Phase Two.

00:27:47.601 --> 00:27:49.069 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Okay!

00:27:49.102 --> 00:27:50.604 position:19% line:89% align:start
Filtering stage, begin.

00:27:50.637 --> 00:27:54.475 position:24% line:83% align:start
Vector resolution,
25% higher than last time.

00:27:54.508 --> 00:27:57.177 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's good.
Maybe we can make it.

00:27:57.211 --> 00:27:59.246 position:13% line:89% align:start
Choose the algorithm well.

00:27:59.279 --> 00:28:00.747 position:30% line:89% align:start
[student] Okay.

00:28:00.781 --> 00:28:02.416 position:10% line:89% align:start
Takuya, what's the algorithm?

00:28:02.449 --> 00:28:04.685 position:16% line:83% align:start
A modified filtering for
extracting groups.

00:28:04.718 --> 00:28:06.487 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's Ekusun Tsukinoe's thesis.

00:28:06.520 --> 00:28:08.188 position:13% line:89% align:start
[student] Ekusun Tsukinoe?

00:28:08.222 --> 00:28:09.323 position:24% line:89% align:start
The from the Union?

00:28:09.356 --> 00:28:10.457 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:28:10.491 --> 00:28:12.292 position:7% line:89% align:start
How did you... who did you say?

00:28:12.326 --> 00:28:13.427 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Takuya]
Hold on a second, please.

00:28:13.460 --> 00:28:14.628 position:13% line:89% align:start
The reaction's building up.

00:28:14.661 --> 00:28:16.029 position:30% line:89% align:start
And who's that?

00:28:16.063 --> 00:28:17.698 position:19% line:83% align:start
The researcher from the
Union who first...

00:28:17.731 --> 00:28:20.067 position:19% line:83% align:start
proved the existence of
parallel worlds.

00:28:20.100 --> 00:28:21.602 position:19% line:83% align:start
Said to be the designer
of the Tower.

00:28:21.635 --> 00:28:22.569 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Got it!

00:28:22.603 --> 00:28:26.473 position:21% line:83% align:start
XA, YC, ZC: confirmed
exposure reactions.

00:28:26.507 --> 00:28:29.276 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] There are five,
no, six branch universes!

00:28:29.309 --> 00:28:33.347 position:19% line:83% align:start
Six, huh? Alright then,
begin the harmonization stage.

00:28:33.380 --> 00:28:35.582 position:19% line:89% align:start
Beginning Phase Three.

00:28:35.616 --> 00:28:37.584 position:10% line:83% align:start
And starting the approach to
connect closest parallel world.

00:28:39.086 --> 00:28:40.254 position:21% line:89% align:start
[student] Roger that!

00:28:45.659 --> 00:28:47.628 position:33% line:89% align:start
He's so fast!

00:28:47.661 --> 00:28:49.530 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] Shirakawa is the
closest one.

00:28:49.563 --> 00:28:52.165 position:16% line:83% align:start
Twelve more Exa to reach
the connectable territory,

00:28:52.199 --> 00:28:55.602 position:16% line:89% align:start
11... 10... 9.4... 9.2...

00:28:55.636 --> 00:28:57.271 position:38% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:28:57.304 --> 00:28:59.306 position:27% line:89% align:start
It got connected!

00:28:59.339 --> 00:29:02.142 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Takuya]
Successful connection to one of
the nearby branch universes.

00:29:02.175 --> 00:29:04.177 position:13% line:89% align:start
Exposure reactions stable.

00:29:04.211 --> 00:29:06.446 position:27% line:83% align:start
Good. Move on to
conversion stage.

00:29:07.447 --> 00:29:09.216 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] Starting the
4th Phase,

00:29:09.249 --> 00:29:11.285 position:27% line:83% align:start
space replacement
with the parallel world.

00:29:11.318 --> 00:29:13.387 position:10% line:83% align:start
So that spiral is the Tower,
I take it?

00:29:13.420 --> 00:29:14.421 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yes, that's right.

00:29:14.454 --> 00:29:16.790 position:21% line:83% align:start
We'll replace several
square inches of space

00:29:16.824 --> 00:29:19.159 position:24% line:83% align:start
in the center with
that of a different universe.

00:29:19.192 --> 00:29:22.830 position:16% line:77% align:start
[Arisaka] I've confirmed
a disparate matter conversion
of 60 nanoradius space.

00:29:22.864 --> 00:29:24.364 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's expanding rapidly.

00:29:24.398 --> 00:29:26.400 position:27% line:83% align:start
Naked eye visual
confirmation soon.

00:29:26.433 --> 00:29:28.535 position:33% line:83% align:start
That one part
is a completely different space

00:29:28.569 --> 00:29:30.704 position:35% line:83% align:start
composed of
a different universe.

00:29:30.737 --> 00:29:34.341 position:7% line:83% align:start
Is this the same operation that
the Ezo Tower's doing?

00:29:34.374 --> 00:29:37.611 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yes, although that is on a much
larger scale.

00:29:37.644 --> 00:29:40.280 position:10% line:83% align:start
We're still at a point where
we only succeed once every

00:29:40.314 --> 00:29:43.717 position:10% line:83% align:start
few tries replacing the space
the size of a grain of sand.

00:29:50.524 --> 00:29:51.525 position:21% line:89% align:start
We've got a problem.

00:29:51.893 --> 00:29:53.126 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's not good!

00:29:54.062 --> 00:29:54.862 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] Exposure
reactions decreasing.

00:29:54.896 --> 00:29:55.729 position:21% line:83% align:start
We can't keep up the
connection...

00:29:55.762 --> 00:29:57.497 position:19% line:83% align:start
with the parallel world
any longer.

00:29:59.466 --> 00:30:01.635 position:41% line:89% align:start
[beep]

00:30:07.641 --> 00:30:09.276 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] The wave
function converged.

00:30:09.309 --> 00:30:11.445 position:24% line:83% align:start
The branch universe
completely disappeared.

00:30:11.478 --> 00:30:14.816 position:16% line:83% align:start
We succeeded in replacing
1.3mm of disparate matter.

00:30:21.622 --> 00:30:24.224 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door opening]

00:30:24.257 --> 00:30:25.359 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Have a good day.

00:30:25.392 --> 00:30:26.326 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Arisaka] Oh, you, too.

00:30:26.360 --> 00:30:29.763 position:24% line:83% align:start
Professor Tomizawa,
is Shirakawa free now?

00:30:29.796 --> 00:30:32.766 position:19% line:83% align:start
He is. You two sure are
spending a lot of time together.

00:30:32.799 --> 00:30:34.301 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Maki]
You're the one who asked me

00:30:34.334 --> 00:30:36.570 position:21% line:83% align:start
to be with him until
he gets used to this place.

00:30:36.603 --> 00:30:38.772 position:10% line:89% align:start
Did I? Oh, by the way, Maki,

00:30:38.806 --> 00:30:40.842 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm going to Tokyo on
business tomorrow.

00:30:40.875 --> 00:30:42.776 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Maki] It's the research report
meeting, right?

00:30:42.810 --> 00:30:46.680 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] That too, but it
seems they found the key.

00:30:46.713 --> 00:30:49.483 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Maki] The key? The one
you told me about before?

00:30:49.516 --> 00:30:50.717 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] Yeah.

00:30:50.751 --> 00:30:53.153 position:13% line:83% align:start
Your Brain Science team may
start putting in longer hours.

00:30:53.687 --> 00:30:55.722 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door opening]

00:30:55.756 --> 00:30:57.290 position:41% line:89% align:start
Maki...

00:31:05.265 --> 00:31:07.902 position:24% line:83% align:start
The military seems
to be here a lot.

00:31:07.935 --> 00:31:10.337 position:19% line:83% align:start
The one in the suit is
probably NSA.

00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:11.772 position:44% line:89% align:start
NSA?

00:31:11.806 --> 00:31:13.473 position:10% line:89% align:start
The National Security Agency.

00:31:13.507 --> 00:31:16.878 position:7% line:83% align:start
I see. There have been a lot of
terrorism rumors lately.

00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:22.416 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Did it go well today?

00:31:22.449 --> 00:31:24.284 position:27% line:89% align:start
Not well enough.

00:31:24.317 --> 00:31:26.821 position:7% line:83% align:start
Best we can do is barely naked
eye visual replacement.

00:31:26.854 --> 00:31:29.623 position:13% line:83% align:start
And we're still far behind
the Union's Tower.

00:31:29.656 --> 00:31:32.626 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Maki] You can't help it since
they're so far ahead of us.

00:31:32.659 --> 00:31:35.562 position:24% line:83% align:start
And they have been,
even with basic physics.

00:31:35.595 --> 00:31:36.864 position:21% line:89% align:start
Since the beginning.

00:31:37.865 --> 00:31:39.033 position:41% line:89% align:start
[ding]

00:31:42.669 --> 00:31:44.271 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] We don't know why
the disparate matter conversion

00:31:44.304 --> 00:31:46.673 position:19% line:83% align:start
stops at a 2 km radius
point from the Tower.

00:31:47.975 --> 00:31:50.978 position:13% line:83% align:start
If it's to attack enemies,
it doesn't work.

00:31:51.012 --> 00:31:53.915 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's function may be suspended
by some accident...

00:31:53.948 --> 00:31:57.317 position:19% line:83% align:start
Or maybe it's simply an
experimental facility.

00:31:57.350 --> 00:31:59.252 position:27% line:83% align:start
Or the disparate
matter conversion itself

00:31:59.286 --> 00:32:02.456 position:21% line:83% align:start
is a function that's
somehow out of control.

00:32:02.489 --> 00:32:05.592 position:10% line:83% align:start
Professor Tomizawa says there
may be some external cause

00:32:05.625 --> 00:32:07.527 position:19% line:83% align:start
that's suppressing the
Tower's function.

00:32:15.602 --> 00:32:17.905 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Hey, Shirakawa...
What are you doing tomorrow?

00:32:17.939 --> 00:32:20.474 position:24% line:83% align:start
Your high school's
on break, right?

00:32:20.507 --> 00:32:22.342 position:27% line:83% align:start
There's something
I want to research.

00:32:22.375 --> 00:32:23.477 position:30% line:89% align:start
At the library?

00:32:23.510 --> 00:32:25.980 position:24% line:83% align:start
No. I'm going to a
friend's factory.

00:32:26.013 --> 00:32:27.882 position:16% line:83% align:start
What do you mean you want
to see the factory?

00:32:27.915 --> 00:32:29.349 position:19% line:89% align:start
We don't do tours here!

00:32:29.382 --> 00:32:31.018 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh? What'd you say?

00:32:31.052 --> 00:32:33.587 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] A girl? How old is she?

00:32:33.620 --> 00:32:35.890 position:21% line:89% align:start
I don't really know.

00:32:35.923 --> 00:32:38.425 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I think she's kind
of pretty though...

00:32:38.458 --> 00:32:40.794 position:13% line:83% align:start
Okay! Then I'll be waiting
for ya.

00:32:57.912 --> 00:32:59.346 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Wow.

00:32:59.379 --> 00:33:01.381 position:19% line:89% align:start
What amazing antennas!

00:33:02.749 --> 00:33:04.018 position:21% line:83% align:start
Well, I've got to be
honest with you,

00:33:04.051 --> 00:33:06.020 position:24% line:83% align:start
some of them aren't
exactly legal.

00:33:06.053 --> 00:33:08.588 position:10% line:83% align:start
But they can connect to some
pretty interesting places.

00:33:08.622 --> 00:33:09.756 position:38% line:89% align:start
I bet...

00:33:13.861 --> 00:33:16.363 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] And you specialize
in brain research,

00:33:16.396 --> 00:33:17.464 position:16% line:89% align:start
is that right Miss Maki?

00:33:17.497 --> 00:33:20.935 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Yes. Things like
memories, sleep, dreams...

00:33:20.968 --> 00:33:23.737 position:35% line:77% align:start
[worker b]
You work at the same research
lab as Takuya, don't you?

00:33:23.770 --> 00:33:26.040 position:24% line:83% align:start
I thought you were
researching the Tower.

00:33:26.073 --> 00:33:28.508 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Yes, I do research
on the Tower...

00:33:28.542 --> 00:33:30.077 position:27% line:89% align:start
How can I put it?

00:33:30.111 --> 00:33:33.780 position:13% line:83% align:start
We both do research dealing
with parallel worlds.

00:33:33.815 --> 00:33:35.950 position:13% line:89% align:start
[worker b] Parallel worlds?

00:33:35.983 --> 00:33:38.785 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, just like a person
dreams at night,

00:33:38.820 --> 00:33:41.555 position:13% line:89% align:start
the universe also "dreams".

00:33:41.588 --> 00:33:44.091 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Maki] This world's hiding
various possibilities of...

00:33:44.125 --> 00:33:47.094 position:10% line:83% align:start
It-could-have-been-like-this
in its dreams.

00:33:47.128 --> 00:33:50.097 position:7% line:83% align:start
We call them "parallel worlds"
or "branch universes."

00:33:52.934 --> 00:33:54.869 position:10% line:83% align:start
My research is to investigate
the effects

00:33:54.902 --> 00:33:56.037 position:16% line:89% align:start
that the parallel worlds

00:33:56.070 --> 00:34:00.074 position:19% line:83% align:start
have on people's brains
and dreams.

00:34:00.107 --> 00:34:02.109 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Maki] The dominant view is
that the Union's Tower

00:34:02.143 --> 00:34:05.412 position:27% line:83% align:start
is also observing
those same things.

00:34:05.445 --> 00:34:07.380 position:27% line:83% align:start
While we can now
observe parallel worlds

00:34:07.414 --> 00:34:08.883 position:27% line:89% align:start
using technology,

00:34:08.916 --> 00:34:11.551 position:16% line:83% align:start
the brains of life forms
may have been perceiving it

00:34:11.585 --> 00:34:14.588 position:24% line:83% align:start
unconsciously from
ancient times.

00:34:14.621 --> 00:34:17.757 position:5% line:83% align:start
The information about the branch
universes that comes and goes

00:34:17.791 --> 00:34:19.726 position:13% line:83% align:start
at the quantum level within
the brain...

00:34:19.759 --> 00:34:21.394 position:5% line:89% align:start
may just be the source of things

00:34:21.428 --> 00:34:24.098 position:27% line:83% align:start
that people call
"premonition" or "precognition".

00:34:24.131 --> 00:34:25.665 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'm researching
things like that.

00:34:25.699 --> 00:34:27.467 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Wow.

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:31.438 position:10% line:83% align:start
The dreams of the universe...
Sounds very romantic to me.

00:34:31.471 --> 00:34:32.739 position:19% line:89% align:start
[in unison] "Romantic"?

00:34:32.772 --> 00:34:34.008 position:24% line:89% align:start
Problem with that?

00:34:35.508 --> 00:34:37.945 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm very impressed with you,
Miss Maki.

00:34:37.979 --> 00:34:41.148 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] A government advisory
counsel researcher at your age.

00:34:41.182 --> 00:34:42.549 position:35% line:89% align:start
Why thanks.

00:34:42.582 --> 00:34:45.186 position:13% line:83% align:start
But since I've admired the
Tower for years,

00:34:45.219 --> 00:34:47.822 position:21% line:83% align:start
it's very fulfilling
work for me.

00:34:47.855 --> 00:34:50.858 position:19% line:83% align:start
I've admired it myself.
You and I have a lot in common.

00:34:50.892 --> 00:34:53.861 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Shirakawa's the one
who's truly admirable!

00:34:53.895 --> 00:34:55.997 position:27% line:83% align:start
He's the youngest
outside researcher!

00:34:56.030 --> 00:34:59.901 position:16% line:83% align:start
And his enthusiasm, well,
he's just so cool!

00:34:59.934 --> 00:35:04.071 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Uh... No, I'm not...
I'm not that cool actually.

00:35:09.476 --> 00:35:11.778 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Maki] I'd better get going now.

00:35:11.812 --> 00:35:13.647 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh my gosh, I'm so sorry.

00:35:13.680 --> 00:35:15.883 position:33% line:83% align:start
It looks like
I ate most of them.

00:35:15.917 --> 00:35:17.517 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] That's all right.

00:35:19.186 --> 00:35:21.989 position:16% line:83% align:start
Takuya, are you going to
the city?

00:35:22.023 --> 00:35:24.091 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Yeah,
I'm taking Maki home.

00:35:24.125 --> 00:35:25.792 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Do you mind giving
me a lift?

00:35:25.826 --> 00:35:27.494 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Maki and worker] What?
[Takuya] Okay.

00:35:27.527 --> 00:35:28.695 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Maki and worker] What?!

00:35:40.908 --> 00:35:42.810 position:16% line:83% align:start
You can just drop me off
at the station.

00:35:42.843 --> 00:35:44.879 position:10% line:89% align:start
What? You're not going back?

00:35:44.912 --> 00:35:47.081 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'll be going to Tokyo on
business tomorrow.

00:35:49.516 --> 00:35:50.617 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Mr. Okabe...

00:35:50.650 --> 00:35:52.552 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Yeah?

00:35:52.585 --> 00:35:55.256 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Have you thought about
what I asked you?

00:35:55.289 --> 00:35:56.790 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] What was that?

00:35:56.824 --> 00:35:58.758 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] About Uilta.

00:35:58.792 --> 00:36:01.228 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Ah.
You're awfully persistent.

00:36:01.262 --> 00:36:03.965 position:13% line:83% align:start
It looks to me like you're
working hard at the lab.

00:36:03.998 --> 00:36:06.033 position:30% line:83% align:start
That work seems
worthwhile, right?

00:36:06.067 --> 00:36:07.902 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] That's not really
the case.

00:36:07.935 --> 00:36:10.637 position:10% line:83% align:start
I just need to settle matters
with that Tower...

00:36:14.574 --> 00:36:16.944 position:24% line:89% align:start
[beep, beep, beep]

00:36:16.978 --> 00:36:18.913 position:13% line:89% align:start
[nurse] What's the matter?

00:36:18.946 --> 00:36:22.917 position:10% line:77% align:start
Nothing. I just didn't think
you could see the Tower
from Tokyo, as well.

00:36:22.950 --> 00:36:25.853 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yeah, there are days
like that...

00:36:25.886 --> 00:36:27.855 position:30% line:83% align:start
The air's quite
clear today, so...

00:36:27.888 --> 00:36:29.622 position:19% line:89% align:start
This way, please, Sir.

00:36:34.862 --> 00:36:36.230 position:24% line:83% align:start
[doctor] That's the
progression of her condition

00:36:36.263 --> 00:36:38.265 position:33% line:83% align:start
since she was
admitted to this hospital.

00:36:38.299 --> 00:36:41.168 position:7% line:83% align:start
The onset was in the summer of
her third year in middle school.

00:36:41.202 --> 00:36:42.602 position:21% line:89% align:start
The cause is unknown.

00:36:42.635 --> 00:36:44.872 position:10% line:83% align:start
The hours of sleep gradually
got longer,

00:36:44.905 --> 00:36:46.307 position:7% line:89% align:start
and she was able to stay awake

00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:49.176 position:16% line:83% align:start
for only limited periods
of time.

00:36:49.210 --> 00:36:52.880 position:16% line:83% align:start
This girl has been asleep
for three years.

00:36:52.913 --> 00:36:55.149 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're telling me she's having
some sort of dream?

00:36:55.182 --> 00:36:57.584 position:16% line:83% align:start
That's what the recorded
brain waves show.

00:36:57.617 --> 00:36:59.619 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hmm. The DNA test?

00:36:59.652 --> 00:37:01.255 position:33% line:89% align:start
On page six.

00:37:02.857 --> 00:37:04.225 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yes, I see...

00:37:04.258 --> 00:37:08.129 position:21% line:83% align:start
She's from a divided
family? Fine.

00:37:08.162 --> 00:37:09.629 position:10% line:89% align:start
This is the request document

00:37:09.662 --> 00:37:11.598 position:10% line:83% align:start
from the Ministry of Health,
Labor and Welfare.

00:37:11.631 --> 00:37:13.100 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] As soon as the
transfer date is decided,

00:37:13.134 --> 00:37:15.702 position:24% line:83% align:start
you'll receive the
official documents.

00:37:15.735 --> 00:37:17.570 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's this letter?

00:37:17.604 --> 00:37:18.906 position:13% line:83% align:start
[doctor] Something that the
patient was writing...

00:37:18.939 --> 00:37:21.075 position:19% line:83% align:start
at the beginning of her
hospitalization.

00:37:21.108 --> 00:37:22.243 position:27% line:89% align:start
Did you read it?

00:37:22.276 --> 00:37:23.543 position:33% line:89% align:start
[doctor] No.

00:37:24.211 --> 00:37:25.712 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] Emishi Plant...

00:37:50.404 --> 00:37:53.808 position:35% line:77% align:start
[Tomizawa]
Thus, by detecting the disparity
of the multiple universes...

00:37:53.841 --> 00:37:56.377 position:19% line:83% align:start
that keep branching off
in its path,

00:37:56.410 --> 00:38:00.247 position:10% line:83% align:start
a highly accurate prediction
of the future becomes possible.

00:38:00.281 --> 00:38:02.049 position:5% line:83% align:start
The ultimate goal of my research
lab lies here as well.

00:38:03.750 --> 00:38:05.953 position:16% line:83% align:start
This isn't a conventional
theoretical model,

00:38:05.986 --> 00:38:07.955 position:19% line:89% align:start
nor probability theory,

00:38:07.988 --> 00:38:12.193 position:16% line:77% align:start
but entirely information
that is based on the results
of the actual future.

00:38:12.226 --> 00:38:14.095 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] So the impact
of this matter,

00:38:14.128 --> 00:38:17.630 position:16% line:83% align:start
on key decision making in
politics and military affairs,

00:38:17.664 --> 00:38:19.366 position:10% line:89% align:start
will likely be incalculable.

00:38:19.400 --> 00:38:22.403 position:7% line:83% align:start
I believe you can all draw your
own conclusions.

00:38:22.436 --> 00:38:25.239 position:7% line:83% align:start
But on the other hand, we have
no other choice but to think...

00:38:25.272 --> 00:38:26.841 position:13% line:89% align:start
that the applied technology

00:38:26.874 --> 00:38:29.709 position:19% line:83% align:start
of the Quantum-Gravity
theory on the Union side...

00:38:29.742 --> 00:38:32.847 position:7% line:83% align:start
has reached such a high level,
that we're no match for them.

00:38:32.880 --> 00:38:35.816 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's generally assumed that the
construction of the Ezo Tower

00:38:35.850 --> 00:38:37.650 position:21% line:89% align:start
was started in 1974,

00:38:37.684 --> 00:38:39.053 position:7% line:89% align:start
after the North-South division,

00:38:39.086 --> 00:38:42.156 position:16% line:83% align:start
with operations beginning
around 1996.

00:38:45.893 --> 00:38:48.095 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Ironic that
mainlander, Ekusun Tsukinoe,

00:38:48.129 --> 00:38:49.864 position:27% line:83% align:start
played a central
role in the design.

00:38:49.897 --> 00:38:51.866 position:24% line:83% align:start
Next, I'll explain
new experiments

00:38:51.899 --> 00:38:53.766 position:10% line:89% align:start
for parallel world detection.

00:38:56.103 --> 00:38:58.873 position:13% line:77% align:start
[Tomizawa] I thought there
was someone in the audience
with a bad attitude.

00:38:58.906 --> 00:39:00.407 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] I was listening
to your talk,

00:39:00.441 --> 00:39:02.076 position:7% line:89% align:start
and from what I can understand,

00:39:02.109 --> 00:39:05.146 position:5% line:83% align:start
you want to look into the dreams
God's having, is that right?

00:39:05.179 --> 00:39:07.780 position:27% line:83% align:start
Do a little dream
reading, as it were.

00:39:07.815 --> 00:39:09.850 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Well, that's more
or less correct.

00:39:09.884 --> 00:39:10.985 position:30% line:89% align:start
You interested?

00:39:11.018 --> 00:39:13.120 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] I've prepared a bid.

00:39:13.154 --> 00:39:15.389 position:10% line:83% align:start
You know, it's been a while.
How about going out tonight?

00:39:19.894 --> 00:39:23.297 position:35% line:77% align:start
[Tomizawa]
Shirakawa's excellent.
He's certainly got aptitude.

00:39:23.330 --> 00:39:25.232 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] You're glad you talked
to him, aren't you?

00:39:25.266 --> 00:39:29.436 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Yeah. But since when
did you start student placement?

00:39:29.470 --> 00:39:33.040 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Well, you could say
they're special to me.

00:39:33.073 --> 00:39:35.176 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] <i>They're</i> special?

00:39:35.209 --> 00:39:38.312 position:10% line:77% align:start
Yeah. There's another student
of mine that I'm getting
kind of worried about.

00:39:38.345 --> 00:39:41.482 position:24% line:83% align:start
Can't seem to make
contact with him.

00:39:41.515 --> 00:39:44.051 position:13% line:83% align:start
The two of them were making
an airplane together.

00:39:44.084 --> 00:39:46.020 position:7% line:89% align:start
That brings back some memories!

00:39:46.053 --> 00:39:48.189 position:7% line:89% align:start
Is that why you came to Tokyo?

00:39:48.222 --> 00:39:50.024 position:16% line:83% align:start
I thought it was another
matter entirely.

00:39:50.057 --> 00:39:52.159 position:16% line:89% align:start
What'd you think it was?

00:39:52.193 --> 00:39:53.360 position:27% line:89% align:start
The Uilta matter.

00:39:54.794 --> 00:39:57.865 position:24% line:83% align:start
Actually, it is the
main reason.

00:39:57.898 --> 00:40:01.035 position:13% line:83% align:start
Going to be able to get our
hands on a PL outer-shell bomb.

00:40:01.068 --> 00:40:02.870 position:13% line:89% align:start
Don't ask me where though.

00:40:02.903 --> 00:40:05.272 position:10% line:83% align:start
I have an idea, more or less,
without asking.

00:40:05.306 --> 00:40:09.776 position:7% line:83% align:start
And so what? Want to ask me if
they work against the Tower?

00:40:09.810 --> 00:40:11.512 position:41% line:89% align:start
Maybe.

00:40:11.545 --> 00:40:13.746 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I think they'll work.

00:40:13.780 --> 00:40:17.151 position:16% line:83% align:start
The exterior of the Tower
will likely vaporize.

00:40:17.184 --> 00:40:20.454 position:10% line:77% align:start
And there's reason to believe
the interior is made up of
nanonet ribbons.

00:40:20.487 --> 00:40:23.924 position:24% line:83% align:start
It'll probably fall
down in flames.

00:40:23.958 --> 00:40:27.895 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yup... PL outer-shell bombs
may be most suitable.

00:40:27.928 --> 00:40:29.129 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:40:32.566 --> 00:40:36.804 position:16% line:77% align:start
But such action by Uilta
may raise the chance
of starting a war...

00:40:36.837 --> 00:40:38.205 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Why don't you
pass on it?

00:40:38.239 --> 00:40:39.807 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] That's why we'll do it.

00:40:39.840 --> 00:40:41.208 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Is this
matter decided?

00:40:41.242 --> 00:40:43.377 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] More or less.

00:40:43.410 --> 00:40:47.448 position:19% line:77% align:start
Since there are so many
higher-ups who are anxious
to start a war.

00:40:47.481 --> 00:40:51.452 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Wasn't your ideology
North-South unification?

00:40:51.485 --> 00:40:53.786 position:27% line:89% align:start
And it still is.

00:40:53.821 --> 00:40:56.490 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] I do feel it's too
valuable to be destroyed.

00:40:56.523 --> 00:40:57.591 position:19% line:89% align:start
From the Alliance side,

00:40:57.625 --> 00:41:00.527 position:7% line:83% align:start
it's fruit of technologies are
almost unbelievable.

00:41:00.561 --> 00:41:03.330 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's just standing there
at most with no real effect.

00:41:03.364 --> 00:41:04.498 position:38% line:89% align:start
So uh...

00:41:04.531 --> 00:41:06.133 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't hide it from me.

00:41:06.166 --> 00:41:08.402 position:13% line:83% align:start
That Tower's not operating
right now,

00:41:08.435 --> 00:41:12.940 position:16% line:77% align:start
but there's a possibility
it's a weapon that'll reverse
the surrounding space...

00:41:12.973 --> 00:41:14.341 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] So you knew?

00:41:14.375 --> 00:41:15.476 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Yeah.

00:41:15.509 --> 00:41:17.444 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] I like that view,
though... to be honest.

00:41:19.380 --> 00:41:22.916 position:13% line:83% align:start
Every so often, I run into
romantic guys just like you.

00:41:25.185 --> 00:41:27.921 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Oka-chan, can I ask
you a question?

00:41:27.955 --> 00:41:29.056 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Sure.

00:41:29.089 --> 00:41:30.291 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] A while back,

00:41:30.324 --> 00:41:33.027 position:7% line:83% align:start
a person who may be related to
the secret of that Tower...

00:41:33.060 --> 00:41:34.161 position:30% line:89% align:start
was discovered.

00:41:34.194 --> 00:41:35.296 position:41% line:89% align:start
Really?

00:41:35.329 --> 00:41:38.032 position:27% line:83% align:start
A girl, actually.
Still in her teens.

00:41:38.065 --> 00:41:39.066 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] I see.

00:41:40.167 --> 00:41:41.268 position:44% line:89% align:start
And?

00:41:41.302 --> 00:41:43.537 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Is she someone
you know?

00:41:43.570 --> 00:41:48.142 position:30% line:89% align:start
[running water]

00:41:48.175 --> 00:41:50.244 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] I don't mean to be
nagging you about this,

00:41:50.277 --> 00:41:53.147 position:16% line:77% align:start
but it'd be best to keep
this information about her
from Shirakawa...

00:41:53.180 --> 00:41:54.448 position:24% line:89% align:start
until we know more.

00:41:54.481 --> 00:41:56.517 position:7% line:89% align:start
Especially if they were close.

00:41:56.550 --> 00:41:59.320 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] He'll find
out eventually.

00:41:59.353 --> 00:42:01.855 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Even so, I wouldn't
worry him right now.

00:42:01.889 --> 00:42:04.558 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's already within the
jurisdiction of the NSA.

00:42:04.591 --> 00:42:06.593 position:10% line:83% align:start
It'd be best if you kept your
nose out of it.

00:42:08.996 --> 00:42:11.565 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] What this universe
dreams about, though...

00:42:11.598 --> 00:42:13.000 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yes...

00:42:13.033 --> 00:42:14.601 position:5% line:89% align:start
I would like to see that, too...

00:42:21.175 --> 00:42:24.611 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>A cold,</i>
 <i>deep wind blew there...</i>

00:42:24.645 --> 00:42:29.350 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>a wind that seemed as if it had</i>
 <i>come from a far away universe.</i>

00:42:29.383 --> 00:42:32.519 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>And the air had the smell</i>
 <i>of a different universe.</i>

00:43:26.006 --> 00:43:27.374 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>The sky... clouds...</i>

00:43:27.408 --> 00:43:29.143 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>and a collapsed town...</i>

00:43:30.577 --> 00:43:33.680 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>No matter how far I walk,</i>
 <i>there's no one.</i>

00:43:37.251 --> 00:43:38.585 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>I feel cold...</i>

00:43:40.521 --> 00:43:42.689 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>Why am I in a place like this?</i>

00:43:44.158 --> 00:43:45.559 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Somebody...</i>

00:43:45.592 --> 00:43:47.194 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Hey, somebody!</i>

00:43:48.328 --> 00:43:50.063 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Hiroki...</i>

00:43:54.601 --> 00:44:00.941 position:27% line:89% align:start
[chalk on board]

00:44:04.478 --> 00:44:06.046 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>That dream again...</i>

00:44:06.680 --> 00:44:10.217 position:33% line:89% align:start
[school bell]

00:44:13.754 --> 00:44:17.524 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>In the end, we didn't</i>
 <i>fly the</i> Bella Ciela.

00:44:20.027 --> 00:44:22.529 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>In its own way,</i>
 <i>it was so shocking...</i>

00:44:22.563 --> 00:44:24.998 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>that Sayuri disappeared</i>
 <i>three years ago</i>

00:44:25.032 --> 00:44:26.667 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>without saying anything</i>
 <i>to either of us</i> .

00:44:28.235 --> 00:44:30.537 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>And I think we were</i>
 <i>upset ourselves,</i>

00:44:30.571 --> 00:44:33.207 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>because we stopped building</i>
 <i>the airplane because of that.</i>

00:44:35.142 --> 00:44:36.743 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>After graduating</i>
 <i>from middle school,</i>

00:44:36.777 --> 00:44:40.347 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Takuya entered a high school</i>
 <i>in Aomori Prefecture,</i>

00:44:40.380 --> 00:44:43.383 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>and I came to a high</i>
 <i>school in Tokyo.</i>

00:44:43.417 --> 00:44:46.353 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>It was because I thought</i>
 <i>I wouldn't be able to see</i>
 <i>the Union's Tower...</i>

00:44:48.222 --> 00:44:50.691 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>But it turned out</i>
 <i>to be a disappointment.</i>

00:44:50.724 --> 00:44:52.559 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I could sometimes see</i>
 <i>the Tower from there</i>

00:44:52.593 --> 00:44:53.627 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>when the weather was nice,</i>

00:44:55.762 --> 00:44:58.499 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>On those days...</i>

00:44:58.532 --> 00:45:00.767 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I felt like I was being</i>
 <i>controlled by this heavy</i>

00:45:00.801 --> 00:45:02.703 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>depressed feeling the</i>
 <i>whole day.</i>

00:45:08.275 --> 00:45:09.443 position:33% line:89% align:start
Lot of tanks.

00:45:09.476 --> 00:45:11.245 position:10% line:83% align:start
They're going all the way to
your hometown, aren't they?

00:45:11.278 --> 00:45:12.746 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I guess.

00:45:12.779 --> 00:45:16.517 position:7% line:83% align:start
Hey, it's going slow enough we
could jump on if we wanted,

00:45:16.550 --> 00:45:19.152 position:19% line:83% align:start
stow away, all the way
to Aomori.

00:45:43.410 --> 00:45:45.679 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Sometimes letters from</i>
 <i>Mr. Okabe arrived,</i>

00:45:45.712 --> 00:45:47.414 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>letting me know how</i>
 <i>things were going.</i>

00:45:48.816 --> 00:45:50.384 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I've never written him back.</i>

00:45:53.153 --> 00:45:56.824 position:13% line:89% align:start
[door opening and closing]

00:46:01.295 --> 00:46:04.531 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Every time I get to my room</i>
 <i>and close the door,</i>

00:46:04.565 --> 00:46:07.234 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I feel severe pain in my mind,</i>

00:46:07.267 --> 00:46:08.802 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>as if the bones</i>
 <i>in my entire body</i>

00:46:08.836 --> 00:46:10.604 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>are breaking</i>
 <i>through my skin.</i>

00:46:12.306 --> 00:46:14.174 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I wonder how long it's been...</i>

00:46:14.207 --> 00:46:17.210 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>since I've taken something</i>
 <i>like this on myself.</i>

