tense international relations.

00:46:24.685 --> 00:46:27.354 position:13% line:83% align:start
At the UN Security Council
held on the 19th,

00:46:27.387 --> 00:46:29.389 position:24% line:83% align:start
America once again
requested the Union

00:46:29.423 --> 00:46:31.592 position:13% line:83% align:start
to accept the UN inspection
group for the Tower of-

00:46:31.625 --> 00:46:34.661 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>Living alone,</i>
 <i>the nights felt long.</i>

00:46:34.695 --> 00:46:36.597 position:41% line:77% align:start
[radio]
In response to this, the Union
government showed their stubborn

00:46:36.630 --> 00:46:38.532 position:33% line:83% align:start
attitude with
a firm refusal.

00:46:38.565 --> 00:46:41.668 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>When I couldn't whittle</i>
 <i>away the time very well,</i>

00:46:41.702 --> 00:46:42.971 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I walked to the nearby station,</i>

00:46:43.004 --> 00:46:46.239 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>and killed time pretending that</i>
 <i>I was waiting for someone.</i>

00:46:47.374 --> 00:46:49.209 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>When I grew tired of that,</i>

00:46:49.242 --> 00:46:51.645 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I walked all the way back</i>
 <i>to my room...</i>

00:46:51.678 --> 00:46:53.146 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>as slow as I could.</i>

00:46:56.683 --> 00:46:58.752 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I had friends in high school,</i>

00:46:58.785 --> 00:47:02.222 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>but other than the times I'm</i>
 <i>wearing the school uniform,</i>

00:47:02.255 --> 00:47:03.590 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>I somehow</i>
 <i>couldn't bring myself</i>

00:47:03.624 --> 00:47:06.861 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>to want to be around them</i>
 <i>that much.</i>

00:47:06.894 --> 00:47:09.496 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>In a city where more than</i>
 <i>thirty million people live,</i>

00:47:09.529 --> 00:47:11.431 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>come to think of it,</i>

00:47:11.465 --> 00:47:13.533 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>there was no one</i>
 <i>whom I wanted to see</i>

00:47:13.567 --> 00:47:14.902 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>or whom I wanted to</i>
 <i>talk to.</i>

00:47:17.504 --> 00:47:21.809 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>In the midst of those days,</i>
 <i>I sometimes dreamt of Sayuri.</i>

00:47:22.944 --> 00:47:27.180 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>In that dream,</i>
 <i>I would look for her, frantic.</i>

00:47:27.214 --> 00:47:30.550 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>But she was at some cold</i>
 <i>place, all by herself...</i>

00:47:30.584 --> 00:47:32.753 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>And in the end...</i>

00:47:32.786 --> 00:47:34.889 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I would always fail</i>
 <i>to find her.</i>

00:47:34.922 --> 00:47:36.757 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>But Sayuri's aura,</i>

00:47:36.790 --> 00:47:39.259 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>the one that made my</i>
 <i>heart tremble,</i>

00:47:39.292 --> 00:47:42.864 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>remained within my body,</i>
 <i>even after waking up.</i>

00:47:42.897 --> 00:47:44.132 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>Before I knew it,</i>

00:47:44.164 --> 00:47:47.935 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>it was my third winter since</i>
 <i>I had come to Tokyo.</i>

00:47:47.969 --> 00:47:52.539 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>It was as if I was holding my</i>
 <i>breath in deep, cold water...</i>

00:47:52.572 --> 00:47:54.942 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Every day was like that.</i>

00:47:54.976 --> 00:47:56.811 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Only, I am...</i>

00:47:56.844 --> 00:47:58.612 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm the only one...</i>

00:47:58.645 --> 00:48:01.816 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>I'm the only one left</i>
 <i>in the world...</i>

00:48:01.849 --> 00:48:03.517 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's the way I feel.</i>

00:48:04.551 --> 00:48:06.420 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's the way that I feel.</i>

00:48:27.340 --> 00:48:29.342 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] It was my dream to
come to Ezo someday.

00:48:31.344 --> 00:48:32.947 position:16% line:83% align:start
I never thought it would
be this easy.

00:48:32.980 --> 00:48:35.515 position:19% line:83% align:start
Yeah. This is only the
southern tip.

00:48:35.549 --> 00:48:37.584 position:21% line:83% align:start
So you have family on
the Union side?

00:48:37.617 --> 00:48:38.853 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's not that, really.

00:48:40.487 --> 00:48:43.390 position:19% line:83% align:start
You were born after the
North-South Division,

00:48:43.423 --> 00:48:44.992 position:5% line:89% align:start
I can understand how you feel...

00:48:45.026 --> 00:48:46.127 position:16% line:89% align:start
[worker b] Like the boss,

00:48:46.160 --> 00:48:49.262 position:5% line:83% align:start
he got separated from his family
because of the Division.

00:48:49.296 --> 00:48:51.698 position:7% line:83% align:start
So I'm sure he's got different
feelings on the issue.

00:48:51.732 --> 00:48:53.467 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yeah? Is that so?

00:48:55.036 --> 00:48:56.838 position:19% line:83% align:start
[worker b] But I didn't
expect this.

00:48:56.871 --> 00:48:58.072 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] What?

00:48:58.106 --> 00:49:00.908 position:10% line:83% align:start
[worker b] I didn't think our
boss would get you involved.

00:49:00.942 --> 00:49:03.911 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I begged him and told
him that...

00:49:03.945 --> 00:49:05.712 position:21% line:83% align:start
if he didn't let me,
I'd turn his ass in.

00:49:05.746 --> 00:49:07.882 position:35% line:83% align:start
You what?!
Man, you live dangerous.

00:49:07.915 --> 00:49:08.983 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:49:17.491 --> 00:49:18.826 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Not good!

00:49:18.860 --> 00:49:20.895 position:27% line:89% align:start
Stupid official!

00:49:20.928 --> 00:49:21.996 position:41% line:89% align:start
[boom]

00:49:24.498 --> 00:49:27.300 position:16% line:83% align:start
They found out about the
secret communication!

00:49:27.334 --> 00:49:28.368 position:38% line:89% align:start
Ship out!

00:49:28.836 --> 00:49:30.437 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:49:39.412 --> 00:49:41.715 position:10% line:83% align:start
[worker b] That was a little
too close that time.

00:49:41.748 --> 00:49:45.052 position:13% line:83% align:start
But now I've got a prospect
on airspace invasion.

00:49:45.086 --> 00:49:48.455 position:13% line:83% align:start
Worthwhile coming all this
way, right?

00:49:48.488 --> 00:49:50.323 position:7% line:89% align:start
[speaker] Boss, there's a ship!

00:49:50.357 --> 00:49:51.424 position:33% line:89% align:start
Patrol boat!

00:49:52.093 --> 00:49:53.493 position:41% line:89% align:start
[siren]

00:49:53.527 --> 00:49:57.664 position:13% line:77% align:start
[patrol] You are violating
the territorial borders
of our country!

00:49:57.697 --> 00:49:59.599 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Starting a war's already
been decided...

00:49:59.633 --> 00:50:01.668 position:7% line:83% align:start
What're they doing? Don't they
know what's going on?!

00:50:01.701 --> 00:50:04.038 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Let's go. Punch it!
[worker c] Yes, Sir!

00:50:04.071 --> 00:50:05.605 position:24% line:83% align:start
Three more minutes
'til the border!

00:50:05.639 --> 00:50:07.741 position:30% line:83% align:start
Sato, Miyagawa,
gun emplacement, now!

00:50:07.774 --> 00:50:09.844 position:7% line:89% align:start
...immediately, or we'll shoot!

00:50:24.025 --> 00:50:25.092 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Takuya!

00:50:25.126 --> 00:50:26.493 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you all right?!

00:50:26.526 --> 00:50:27.594 position:41% line:89% align:start
Takuya!

00:50:41.675 --> 00:50:43.510 position:21% line:89% align:start
Those white wings...

00:50:43.543 --> 00:50:44.812 position:33% line:89% align:start
I know them!

00:51:05.967 --> 00:51:07.667 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>When I wake up,</i>

00:51:07.701 --> 00:51:10.838 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>for a second I don't</i>
 <i>quite understand where I am.</i>

00:51:13.640 --> 00:51:16.476 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I sometimes think that I</i>
 <i>might've come to...</i>

00:51:16.509 --> 00:51:17.711 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>the wrong place.</i>

00:51:21.781 --> 00:51:25.853 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>But now, I feel the dream</i>
 <i>about Sayuri...</i>

00:51:25.887 --> 00:51:29.991 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>is more realistic than</i>
 <i>the reality I'm living.</i>

00:51:30.024 --> 00:51:32.159 position:38% line:89% align:start
[rustle]

00:51:46.773 --> 00:51:48.408 position:19% line:89% align:start
The hospital she's in?

00:51:56.150 --> 00:51:57.550 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>Sayuri...</i>

00:52:21.909 --> 00:52:24.544 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>Hiroki... Takuya...</i>

00:52:24.577 --> 00:52:28.249 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm sorry for disappearing</i>
 <i>without saying anything to you.</i>

00:52:28.282 --> 00:52:33.187 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>I'm disappointed because</i>
 <i>I wanted to spend</i>
 <i>the summer break with you.</i>

00:52:33.220 --> 00:52:36.556 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>When I woke up, I was in</i>
 <i>a hospital in Tokyo,</i>

00:52:36.589 --> 00:52:40.194 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>and I've been in the</i>
 <i>hospital ever since.</i>

00:52:40.227 --> 00:52:42.196 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The people at the hospital</i>
 <i>told me that I should</i>

00:52:42.229 --> 00:52:45.833 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>sever all relationships</i>
 <i>that I had before,</i>

00:52:45.866 --> 00:52:49.070 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>but I'm writing this right now</i>
 <i>after begging them to let me.</i>

00:52:50.871 --> 00:52:54.141 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll send this to Mr. Okabe</i>
 <i>so that you two will read this.</i>

00:53:02.984 --> 00:53:06.087 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>But I don't quite know</i>
 <i>what I should write.</i>

00:53:13.626 --> 00:53:17.131 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I've been having the same</i>
 <i>dream, over and over again.</i>

00:53:21.969 --> 00:53:24.305 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>A dream that I'm alone...</i>

00:53:24.338 --> 00:53:27.241 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>in an empty universe where</i>
 <i>there's no one around.</i>

00:53:28.608 --> 00:53:30.211 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>In that dream, all of me,</i>

00:53:30.244 --> 00:53:32.279 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>fingers, cheeks, fingernails,</i>

00:53:32.313 --> 00:53:33.881 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>heels, even the tips of</i>
 <i>my hair...</i>

00:53:33.914 --> 00:53:35.782 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>ache from such loneliness.</i>

00:53:37.018 --> 00:53:40.087 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>The world filled with warmth,</i>

00:53:40.121 --> 00:53:43.757 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>the one where the three of</i>
 <i>us were together,</i>

00:53:43.790 --> 00:53:47.294 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>seems more like a dream than</i>
 <i>the dream I'm having now.</i>

00:53:49.596 --> 00:53:54.869 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>But I feel that so long as</i>
 <i>I don't lose the memories</i>
 <i>from those days,</i>

00:53:54.902 --> 00:53:58.571 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I may be able to stay</i>
 <i>connected to reality.</i>

00:53:58.605 --> 00:54:01.674 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>If only by a fragile,</i>
 <i>fragile hold.</i>

00:54:02.675 --> 00:54:04.145 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] She changed hospitals?

00:54:04.178 --> 00:54:06.347 position:7% line:89% align:start
[nurse] Yes, about a week ago.

00:54:06.380 --> 00:54:09.616 position:7% line:83% align:start
As for details, you might want
to ask the transfer hospital.

00:54:10.284 --> 00:54:12.053 position:41% line:89% align:start
Okay...

00:54:12.086 --> 00:54:14.989 position:24% line:83% align:start
Um, which room was
Miss Sawatari in?

00:54:18.192 --> 00:54:20.194 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>Hiroki... Takuya...</i>

00:54:21.795 --> 00:54:25.066 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Did that beautiful white</i>
 <i>airplane fly safely?</i>

00:54:26.033 --> 00:54:29.003 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>To that Tower beyond the ocean?</i>

00:54:34.975 --> 00:54:37.644 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>I wonder what this is.</i>

00:54:37.677 --> 00:54:39.847 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's the same air from</i>
 <i>the dream...</i>

00:54:46.753 --> 00:54:48.322 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Sayuri...</i>

00:54:48.989 --> 00:54:50.858 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Are you there?</i>

00:55:09.410 --> 00:55:11.946 position:10% line:83% align:start
[in unison] All this time...
all this time...

00:55:11.979 --> 00:55:13.380 position:21% line:89% align:start
I've been searching!

00:55:27.895 --> 00:55:29.762 position:38% line:89% align:start
Sayuri...

00:55:29.796 --> 00:55:33.300 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I really want to
fulfill my promise this time.

00:55:33.334 --> 00:55:37.838 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'll fly the <i>Bella Ciela</i> to the
Tower with you on board.

00:55:37.872 --> 00:55:41.075 position:7% line:83% align:start
I feel that we'll meet again if
I do that.

00:55:41.108 --> 00:55:44.078 position:13% line:89% align:start
I-I won't leave you alone.

00:55:44.111 --> 00:55:46.746 position:16% line:89% align:start
I won't give up anymore.

00:55:46.779 --> 00:55:50.317 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I'll protect you
forever. I promise.

00:55:52.353 --> 00:55:55.356 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Yes, it's a promise.

00:55:55.389 --> 00:55:58.225 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Let's fly to the
Tower... together.

00:56:05.866 --> 00:56:12.907 position:24% line:89% align:start
[beep, beep, beep]

00:56:14.741 --> 00:56:17.478 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Professor! We need you!

00:56:17.511 --> 00:56:18.879 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] The operational level
of the Tower

00:56:18.913 --> 00:56:20.347 position:16% line:89% align:start
has suddenly been raised!

00:56:20.381 --> 00:56:23.918 position:33% line:77% align:start
The limits of
the disparate matter conversion
are expanding rapidly!

00:56:23.951 --> 00:56:27.421 position:16% line:77% align:start
Conscious activity level
of the subject is increasing
at the same time!

00:56:27.454 --> 00:56:29.490 position:21% line:89% align:start
She may be waking up.

00:56:29.523 --> 00:56:31.292 position:10% line:89% align:start
Professor, could this be...?

00:56:31.325 --> 00:56:33.827 position:7% line:83% align:start
Disparate matter conversion has
exceeded 20 kilometers!

00:56:35.529 --> 00:56:37.031 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Tomizawa] This is...

00:56:37.064 --> 00:56:39.200 position:13% line:83% align:start
Is this going to overwrite
the world?

00:56:43.204 --> 00:56:46.073 position:13% line:83% align:start
Subject conscious level...
it's going down, Sir!

00:56:46.106 --> 00:56:48.976 position:16% line:83% align:start
Speed of disparate matter
conversion... slowing down.

00:56:53.247 --> 00:56:57.351 position:30% line:77% align:start
A 26 km radius
has been overwritten
with a parallel world.

00:56:57.384 --> 00:57:00.454 position:7% line:83% align:start
Subject consciousness also down
to usual levels.

00:57:00.487 --> 00:57:02.722 position:21% line:83% align:start
Her sleep is becoming
stable again.

00:57:03.857 --> 00:57:05.326 position:30% line:89% align:start
Professor, I...

00:57:05.359 --> 00:57:06.594 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:57:06.627 --> 00:57:09.230 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] As we thought, the
subject's sleep was the key...

00:57:09.263 --> 00:57:11.865 position:16% line:83% align:start
that was restraining the
Tower's activity.

00:57:11.899 --> 00:57:15.469 position:7% line:83% align:start
The information of the parallel
world that the Tower captures...

00:57:15.502 --> 00:57:18.472 position:10% line:83% align:start
is flowing into the subject's
dream for now,

00:57:18.505 --> 00:57:21.375 position:24% line:83% align:start
instead of eroding
the surrounding space.

00:57:21.408 --> 00:57:25.546 position:7% line:83% align:start
We must ensure Sayuri Sawatari
keeps dreaming.

00:57:25.579 --> 00:57:28.849 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>I might have just</i>
 <i>been dreaming...</i>

00:57:28.882 --> 00:57:31.485 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Even then, Sayuri's warmth</i>
 <i>that touched my skin</i>

00:57:31.518 --> 00:57:33.887 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>continued to keep</i>
 <i>my body warm.</i>

00:57:35.856 --> 00:57:37.024 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>On that distant day,</i>

00:57:38.425 --> 00:57:40.361 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>we made a promise...</i>

00:57:40.394 --> 00:57:41.428 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>we couldn't keep.</i>

00:57:50.170 --> 00:57:53.140 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Hey, Takuya...

00:57:53.173 --> 00:57:54.575 position:19% line:89% align:start
This may sound strange,

00:57:54.608 --> 00:57:56.277 position:16% line:83% align:start
but you promise you won't
laugh, okay?

00:57:56.310 --> 00:57:59.013 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] What? What is it?
I won't laugh.

00:57:59.046 --> 00:58:00.414 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Then, I'll tell you.

00:58:00.447 --> 00:58:03.917 position:16% line:83% align:start
Um... It's about a dream
I have a lot.

00:58:06.620 --> 00:58:08.022 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] A tall tower?

00:58:08.055 --> 00:58:10.124 position:19% line:89% align:start
Is it the Union Tower?

00:58:10.157 --> 00:58:14.361 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] No. It has a more
crooked and mysterious shape.

00:58:15.262 --> 00:58:17.865 position:10% line:89% align:start
Inside the tower where I am,

00:58:17.898 --> 00:58:20.134 position:7% line:83% align:start
there are many others just like
it, standing all around.

00:58:21.635 --> 00:58:23.470 position:5% line:83% align:start
In the whole area... I know this
for some reason...

00:58:26.540 --> 00:58:30.577 position:19% line:83% align:start
but each one is a whole
entirely separate world.

00:58:30.611 --> 00:58:34.114 position:13% line:83% align:start
A dream that this universe
is having.

00:58:34.148 --> 00:58:36.550 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I can't get out and I
feel so lonely...

00:58:36.583 --> 00:58:39.987 position:16% line:83% align:start
and then when I feel like
my mind will disappear...

00:58:40.020 --> 00:58:42.389 position:19% line:83% align:start
I see a white airplane
in the sky.

00:58:45.059 --> 00:58:46.393 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] A white airplane?

00:58:46.427 --> 00:58:47.995 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Yeah...

00:58:48.028 --> 00:58:49.063 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] And?

00:58:50.164 --> 00:58:51.498 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] That's the end of
the dream.

00:59:01.608 --> 00:59:03.077 position:27% line:89% align:start
[door unlocking]

00:59:07.614 --> 00:59:09.350 position:30% line:89% align:start
Thank goodness!

00:59:09.383 --> 00:59:11.585 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Shirakawa, you're awake.

00:59:11.618 --> 00:59:13.320 position:41% line:89% align:start
Maki...

00:59:13.354 --> 00:59:15.022 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Maki] I was really worried.

00:59:15.055 --> 00:59:16.357 position:30% line:89% align:start
You were? why?

00:59:16.390 --> 00:59:17.658 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Does your shoulder
still hurt?

00:59:17.691 --> 00:59:19.059 position:47% line:89% align:start
No.

00:59:21.462 --> 00:59:22.529 position:35% line:89% align:start
Excuse me.

00:59:25.632 --> 00:59:27.668 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Maki] It seems like your
fever's come down.

00:59:27.701 --> 00:59:30.371 position:30% line:83% align:start
Are you hungry?
Do you want something to eat?

00:59:30.404 --> 00:59:31.972 position:10% line:89% align:start
I brought apples and bananas.

00:59:32.005 --> 00:59:33.674 position:30% line:83% align:start
I also went and
bought some cakes.

00:59:33.707 --> 00:59:34.942 position:21% line:89% align:start
What would you like?

00:59:47.621 --> 00:59:50.457 position:19% line:83% align:start
You can't get in there
with your ID card.

00:59:50.491 --> 00:59:52.259 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Is your injury
better now?

00:59:52.292 --> 00:59:56.063 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Oh, yes. Sorry for
making you worry.

00:59:56.096 --> 00:59:57.231 position:38% line:89% align:start
Listen...

00:59:57.264 --> 00:59:58.999 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] I heard that
Maki told you.

01:00:00.334 --> 01:00:01.935 position:27% line:89% align:start
Want to see her?

01:00:05.272 --> 01:00:08.342 position:13% line:83% align:start
We're speculating that the
reason why she keeps sleeping...

01:00:08.375 --> 01:00:10.210 position:5% line:89% align:start
is because her brain cannot bare

01:00:10.244 --> 01:00:12.246 position:7% line:83% align:start
the information of the parallel
worlds...

01:00:12.279 --> 01:00:14.648 position:10% line:89% align:start
that flows in from the Tower.

01:00:14.681 --> 01:00:15.817 position:19% line:89% align:start
If her sleep is broken,

01:00:15.850 --> 01:00:18.552 position:16% line:83% align:start
I think the world will be
swallowed up in an instant...

01:00:18.585 --> 01:00:22.956 position:7% line:83% align:start
by the parallel worlds with the
Tower at the center of it all.

01:00:22.990 --> 01:00:25.592 position:13% line:83% align:start
Frankly, we don't even know
how to wake her up.

01:00:27.227 --> 01:00:29.062 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] With the war
starting soon,

01:00:29.096 --> 01:00:32.199 position:19% line:77% align:start
it's been decided that
she'll be transferred
to the NSA headquarters,

01:00:32.232 --> 01:00:34.334 position:21% line:83% align:start
in the home country,
within a few days.

01:00:36.036 --> 01:00:39.406 position:13% line:83% align:start
To the Alliance that falls
far behind in this field,

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:41.442 position:16% line:89% align:start
she is a valuable sample.

01:00:45.145 --> 01:00:48.449 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Why does it have
to be Sayuri?

01:00:48.482 --> 01:00:50.651 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] Although there are
more matters that we don't know

01:00:50.684 --> 01:00:52.052 position:16% line:89% align:start
than matters that we do,

01:00:52.085 --> 01:00:54.154 position:30% line:83% align:start
I doubt this is
purely coincidence.

01:00:54.188 --> 01:00:56.223 position:27% line:83% align:start
Ekusun Tsukinoe,
the designer of the Tower,

01:00:56.256 --> 01:00:57.458 position:24% line:89% align:start
is her grandfather.

01:01:02.496 --> 01:01:05.199 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] As you've heard, the
Tower is clearly a weapon.

01:01:05.766 --> 01:01:06.868 position:19% line:89% align:start
For the past 25 years,

01:01:06.901 --> 01:01:09.603 position:10% line:83% align:start
the Tower had become part of
the everyday scenery...

01:01:09.636 --> 01:01:12.172 position:21% line:83% align:start
and it symbolized all
sorts of things.

01:01:12.206 --> 01:01:16.210 position:24% line:83% align:start
Nation. War. Race.
Despair. Admiration.

01:01:16.243 --> 01:01:18.612 position:19% line:83% align:start
Each generation looked
at it differently...

01:01:18.645 --> 01:01:20.013 position:30% line:89% align:start
But regardless,

01:01:20.047 --> 01:01:24.051 position:16% line:77% align:start
it seems everyone saw it
as a symbol of something
beyond their reach.

01:01:24.084 --> 01:01:25.652 position:5% line:89% align:start
Something that can't be changed.

01:01:26.787 --> 01:01:28.755 position:19% line:89% align:start
And as long as they do,

01:01:28.789 --> 01:01:31.258 position:24% line:83% align:start
this world probably
won't change.

01:01:33.126 --> 01:01:34.561 position:24% line:89% align:start
In just three days,

01:01:34.595 --> 01:01:38.765 position:19% line:77% align:start
the American government
will make a declaration of war
to the Union.

01:01:38.799 --> 01:01:43.270 position:24% line:77% align:start
Taking advantage of
the confusion caused by
the start of the war,

01:01:43.303 --> 01:01:46.273 position:16% line:83% align:start
we'll carry out terrorist
bombings on the Tower.

01:01:46.306 --> 01:01:49.776 position:41% line:77% align:start
[Okabe]
We'll invade Ezo airspace
with an unmanned Predator.

01:01:49.811 --> 01:01:53.146 position:10% line:83% align:start
Use a Seeker missile carrying
a PL outer-shell bomb.

01:01:53.180 --> 01:01:56.717 position:7% line:83% align:start
The Uilta Liberation Front will
be disbanded on the same day.

01:01:56.750 --> 01:02:00.254 position:16% line:83% align:start
And today, we close this
factory down as well.

01:02:00.287 --> 01:02:01.722 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

01:02:03.524 --> 01:02:05.225 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Okay.

01:02:05.259 --> 01:02:06.760 position:30% line:89% align:start
Okay, I got it.

01:02:06.793 --> 01:02:08.362 position:19% line:89% align:start
See you tomorrow, then.

01:02:20.207 --> 01:02:21.375 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hey.

01:02:21.408 --> 01:02:23.710 position:16% line:89% align:start
Three years, huh Takuya?

01:02:27.214 --> 01:02:28.482 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] When did you get here?

01:02:28.515 --> 01:02:29.683 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] The day
before yesterday.

01:02:29.716 --> 01:02:32.085 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm sleeping in the
old station right now.

01:02:32.119 --> 01:02:33.253 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Takuya]
The one they closed down?

01:02:33.287 --> 01:02:34.388 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah.

01:02:34.421 --> 01:02:37.157 position:21% line:83% align:start
Takuya, what happened
to your arm?

01:02:37.190 --> 01:02:39.626 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Oh. It's nothing.

01:02:39.660 --> 01:02:42.162 position:27% line:83% align:start
What do you mean,
"it's nothing"?

01:02:42.195 --> 01:02:43.597 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I'll tell you
about it later.

01:02:45.833 --> 01:02:48.435 position:7% line:83% align:start
I wonder if it's closed today.
[meow]

01:02:49.469 --> 01:02:51.171 position:21% line:89% align:start
Chobi! How you doing?

01:02:51.204 --> 01:02:52.739 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's been a while, hasn't it?

01:02:56.310 --> 01:03:00.714 position:30% line:89% align:start
[jets overhead]

01:03:17.364 --> 01:03:19.232 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Fly the <i>Bella Ciela?</i>

01:03:21.335 --> 01:03:22.736 position:21% line:89% align:start
With Sayuri on board?

01:03:22.769 --> 01:03:24.738 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah.

01:03:24.771 --> 01:03:28.275 position:13% line:83% align:start
Another day or so and I'll
be finished assembling it.

01:03:28.308 --> 01:03:31.645 position:16% line:83% align:start
What's left would be the
control software problem.

01:03:31.678 --> 01:03:33.680 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Hold on.
Did you hear what I said?

01:03:33.714 --> 01:03:35.850 position:21% line:83% align:start
Sayuri keeps sleeping
and the Tower is-

01:03:35.883 --> 01:03:39.219 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] The Tower is the target
of the terrorist attack, right?

01:03:39.252 --> 01:03:41.288 position:19% line:83% align:start
That's why I need your
help, Takuya!

01:03:42.522 --> 01:03:45.292 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I told you that
I'd been thinking...

01:03:45.325 --> 01:03:48.762 position:7% line:83% align:start
If I fly to the Tower with her,
I think she'll wake up.

01:03:50.564 --> 01:03:51.765 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] What are you
talking about?

01:03:53.200 --> 01:03:54.735 position:21% line:83% align:start
Did you come back for
such a thing?

01:03:56.603 --> 01:03:58.906 position:27% line:89% align:start
"Such a thing"?!

01:03:58.940 --> 01:04:00.808 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] We made a
promise, remember?

01:04:03.811 --> 01:04:06.647 position:10% line:89% align:start
I have dreams about Sayuri...

01:04:06.680 --> 01:04:10.651 position:7% line:89% align:start
So many times... repeatedly...

01:04:10.684 --> 01:04:12.920 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki]
She was alone in a place
where there was no one around,

01:04:12.954 --> 01:04:15.522 position:10% line:83% align:start
and she told me she couldn't
remember anything.

01:04:16.824 --> 01:04:19.493 position:7% line:89% align:start
But she remembers that promise.

01:04:19.526 --> 01:04:21.495 position:7% line:89% align:start
We promised again in the dream,

01:04:21.528 --> 01:04:24.564 position:16% line:83% align:start
that I'd really take her
to the Tower this time.

01:04:24.598 --> 01:04:27.634 position:13% line:83% align:start
And I-I can't believe it's
just a dream.

01:04:31.839 --> 01:04:34.441 position:24% line:83% align:start
You come back after
three years...

01:04:34.474 --> 01:04:35.542 position:7% line:89% align:start
I wondered what it was about...

01:04:36.911 --> 01:04:38.712 position:16% line:89% align:start
And it was about a dream?

01:04:40.647 --> 01:04:42.850 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I can't even stand
to look at you.

01:04:46.319 --> 01:04:48.321 position:21% line:83% align:start
I don't have time for
this kid stuff.

01:04:50.424 --> 01:04:51.725 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] You're just obsessed.

01:04:53.527 --> 01:04:54.829 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'll help you forget.

01:04:56.998 --> 01:04:58.298 position:38% line:89% align:start
Stop it!

01:04:58.331 --> 01:04:59.599 position:41% line:89% align:start
[bang]

01:05:25.492 --> 01:05:26.693 position:41% line:89% align:start
Takuya!

01:05:28.361 --> 01:05:30.464 position:30% line:89% align:start
Save Sayuri...

01:05:30.497 --> 01:05:31.833 position:24% line:89% align:start
or save the world?

01:05:52.385 --> 01:05:57.557 position:33% line:89% align:start
[school bell]

01:06:13.373 --> 01:06:15.542 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] I, uh,
forgot something.

01:06:16.743 --> 01:06:17.879 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] I see.

01:06:24.051 --> 01:06:25.820 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Aren't you going
home, Sayuri?

01:06:26.553 --> 01:06:28.588 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, yes. I am.

01:06:32.659 --> 01:06:34.694 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Hiroki...

01:06:34.728 --> 01:06:36.998 position:10% line:89% align:start
What happened to your cheek?

01:06:37.031 --> 01:06:39.299 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Oh, I had a little
fight with Takuya.

01:06:40.835 --> 01:06:42.402 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Are you okay?

01:06:42.435 --> 01:06:43.938 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] I'm okay, yeah.

01:06:43.971 --> 01:06:46.473 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm sure we'll make up soon.
Probably.

01:06:48.075 --> 01:06:49.476 position:10% line:89% align:start
Listen, have a good evening.

01:06:49.509 --> 01:06:50.878 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Hiroki!

01:06:50.912 --> 01:06:53.047 position:7% line:89% align:start
A-Are you going to the station?

01:07:02.689 --> 01:07:04.959 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>I always have</i>
 <i>a premonition...</i>

01:07:04.992 --> 01:07:07.327 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>premonition of</i>
 <i>losing something.</i>

01:07:08.863 --> 01:07:12.499 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>The world is so beautiful.</i>

01:07:12.532 --> 01:07:15.502 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>But I feel like I'm the only</i>
 <i>one who's far from it.</i>

01:07:19.706 --> 01:07:21.441 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>But I think that</i>
 <i>at that time,</i>

01:07:21.474 --> 01:07:26.013 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>it looked to me as if Sayuri</i>
 <i>was at the center of</i>
 <i>the brilliant world.</i>

01:07:28.149 --> 01:07:31.384 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Ah. I see.</i>

01:07:31.418 --> 01:07:33.955 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I just felt like I sort</i>
 <i>of understood...</i>

01:07:34.754 --> 01:07:36.824 position:33% line:89% align:start
Something...

01:07:36.858 --> 01:07:38.592 position:19% line:89% align:start
Something important...

01:07:51.038 --> 01:07:53.607 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Hello! Is anyone home?

01:08:02.616 --> 01:08:04.185 position:35% line:89% align:start
Mr. Okabe!

01:08:04.218 --> 01:08:05.685 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's me, Hiroki.

01:08:05.719 --> 01:08:07.121 position:35% line:89% align:start
Mr. Okabe!

01:08:09.522 --> 01:08:11.458 position:7% line:89% align:start
But the contact information...

01:08:28.876 --> 01:08:30.644 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Just as I thought.

01:08:30.677 --> 01:08:33.047 position:10% line:89% align:start
My, Hiroki. How you've grown.

01:08:33.080 --> 01:08:34.514 position:41% line:89% align:start
Okabe?

01:08:34.547 --> 01:08:35.649 position:33% line:89% align:start
What are you-

01:08:35.682 --> 01:08:37.484 position:19% line:89% align:start
I heard it from Takuya.

01:08:37.517 --> 01:08:40.922 position:24% line:83% align:start
Let's see just how
determined you are.

01:08:40.955 --> 01:08:42.823 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] <i>You</i> guys destroy
that Tower.

01:08:44.058 --> 01:08:46.626 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Are the terrorist bombing
rumors true?

01:08:46.660 --> 01:08:48.863 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] I don't know.

01:08:48.896 --> 01:08:50.898 position:13% line:83% align:start
But the start of the war is
probably coming soon...

01:08:50.932 --> 01:08:53.600 position:24% line:89% align:start
and once it starts,

01:08:53.633 --> 01:08:57.805 position:10% line:83% align:start
research on the Tower may be
the last thing we can think of.

01:08:57.838 --> 01:08:59.173 position:33% line:83% align:start
I think that
what Tsukinoe's doing

01:08:59.206 --> 01:09:00.808 position:16% line:83% align:start
and what terrorists like
Uilta are doing...

01:09:00.841 --> 01:09:02.944 position:19% line:89% align:start
may be the same thing.

01:09:02.977 --> 01:09:05.112 position:30% line:83% align:start
Protesting the
North-South division.

01:09:07.148 --> 01:09:10.151 position:21% line:83% align:start
You're so mysterious,
aren't you, Shirakawa?

01:09:10.184 --> 01:09:12.186 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Maki] I feel like you have
a lot of secrets.

01:09:12.219 --> 01:09:14.021 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] No, not at all...

01:09:14.055 --> 01:09:15.990 position:13% line:89% align:start
Sorry. I'll make some tea.

01:09:16.023 --> 01:09:19.193 position:21% line:83% align:start
And then, I'll treat
your wound, okay?

01:09:24.597 --> 01:09:27.767 position:21% line:83% align:start
You seem to get a lot
of wounds these days.

01:09:27.801 --> 01:09:30.037 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sorry.

01:09:30.071 --> 01:09:32.006 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do you have some troubles
or something?

01:09:32.039 --> 01:09:34.141 position:33% line:89% align:start
No, I'm okay.

01:09:35.109 --> 01:09:36.210 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Really...

01:09:41.715 --> 01:09:44.584 position:19% line:89% align:start
He was my best friend.

01:09:44.617 --> 01:09:45.518 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Maki] What?

01:09:45.552 --> 01:09:49.090 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] We admired the
very same things.

01:09:49.123 --> 01:09:50.724 position:13% line:89% align:start
And we had the same goals.

01:09:50.757 --> 01:09:52.792 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Yeah.

01:09:52.827 --> 01:09:55.296 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] But we both went
to different places.

01:09:55.329 --> 01:09:56.964 position:30% line:89% align:start
How can I say?

01:09:56.998 --> 01:10:00.600 position:19% line:83% align:start
I didn't know in which
direction I should go...

01:10:00.633 --> 01:10:03.070 position:10% line:83% align:start
even though the energies and
urges I couldn't understand

01:10:03.104 --> 01:10:04.238 position:27% line:89% align:start
welled up inside.

01:10:05.638 --> 01:10:07.274 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Yeah.

01:10:07.308 --> 01:10:11.678 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] So I was relieved
to join the work at this lab,

01:10:13.314 --> 01:10:17.818 position:7% line:83% align:start
I felt like I'd found something
I should be doing.

01:10:17.852 --> 01:10:20.154 position:19% line:89% align:start
I was glad to meet you.

01:10:24.291 --> 01:10:25.658 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I don't want to
involve you.

01:10:26.894 --> 01:10:28.062 position:7% line:89% align:start
There's something I have to do.

01:10:42.243 --> 01:10:44.812 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] When this...
when this is all over,

01:10:46.679 --> 01:10:47.680 position:24% line:89% align:start
I would like to...

01:10:48.816 --> 01:10:50.184 position:7% line:89% align:start
I would like to see you again.

01:10:52.153 --> 01:10:53.220 position:35% line:89% align:start
Shirakawa!

01:11:22.749 --> 01:11:24.085 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Sayuri...

01:11:24.118 --> 01:11:26.053 position:7% line:89% align:start
Let's go to the promised place.

01:11:26.087 --> 01:11:27.221 position:21% line:89% align:start
This time, for sure.

01:11:35.329 --> 01:11:37.630 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] What's going on,
Oka-chan?

01:11:37.664 --> 01:11:40.101 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're going to use kids
for something like that?

01:11:40.134 --> 01:11:42.036 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] They're the ones who
wanted to do it.

01:11:42.069 --> 01:11:44.171 position:10% line:83% align:start
Besides, the surrounding area
of the Tower

01:11:44.205 --> 01:11:48.042 position:7% line:83% align:start
has been swallowed by what you
call parallel worlds, right?

01:11:48.075 --> 01:11:49.176 position:30% line:83% align:start
No one's going
to die there.

01:11:49.210 --> 01:11:50.743 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Tomizawa] That's no
reason for-

01:11:50.777 --> 01:11:53.080 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Okabe] Calm down, Tomizawa.

01:11:53.114 --> 01:11:55.816 position:24% line:83% align:start
Anyway, by the time
they get back,

01:11:55.850 --> 01:11:57.750 position:13% line:89% align:start
they won't be kids anymore.

01:11:59.386 --> 01:12:02.289 position:24% line:83% align:start
Shall I guess what
you're thinking right now?

01:12:05.792 --> 01:12:08.129 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh boy, oh boy...

01:12:08.162 --> 01:12:09.396 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Okabe] Well then,
I'm hanging up.

01:12:12.166 --> 01:12:14.301 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's finally coming to a climax.

01:12:16.736 --> 01:12:19.706 position:19% line:83% align:start
Is Sayuri really going
to wake up with that?

01:12:19.739 --> 01:12:23.144 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I'm convinced she
will too, now. For some reason.

01:12:23.177 --> 01:12:26.881 position:10% line:83% align:start
The promise from that day is
probably her tie to reality.

01:12:26.914 --> 01:12:31.452 position:7% line:83% align:start
Even now, she's waiting for the
 <i>Bella Ciela</i> in her dream.

01:12:31.485 --> 01:12:34.088 position:7% line:83% align:start
I feel that Hiroki and I always
knew this somehow.

01:12:38.259 --> 01:12:40.227 position:24% line:83% align:start
The <i>Bella Ciela</i> is
a two-seater,

01:12:40.261 --> 01:12:42.897 position:13% line:83% align:start
and I really couldn't pilot
her with this arm.

01:12:42.930 --> 01:12:46.066 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] I'll stay behind and
watch what happens to the Tower.

01:12:48.302 --> 01:12:51.839 position:10% line:83% align:start
I thought it was cold. Looks
like it's snowing again.

01:12:51.872 --> 01:12:53.040 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'll be going now.

01:12:53.073 --> 01:12:55.176 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah. Look at that.

01:12:55.209 --> 01:12:57.411 position:24% line:83% align:start
You two are working
together again.

01:12:57.444 --> 01:12:59.113 position:13% line:89% align:start
Now be good to each other!

01:13:06.753 --> 01:13:08.788 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Which one is it...
Is this it?

01:13:19.967 --> 01:13:22.102 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door opening]

01:13:45.392 --> 01:13:47.861 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Did you hear it
from Mr. Okabe?

01:13:47.895 --> 01:13:49.263 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah.

01:13:55.936 --> 01:13:57.770 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Takuya.

01:13:57.805 --> 01:14:01.108 position:7% line:83% align:start
Which version of BIOS you think
I should use?

01:14:01.141 --> 01:14:03.244 position:19% line:83% align:start
You changed the ladder,
didn't you?

01:14:03.277 --> 01:14:04.411 position:5% line:89% align:start
I don't have the one after that.

01:14:07.982 --> 01:14:09.917 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's in this.

01:14:09.950 --> 01:14:12.119 position:24% line:83% align:start
It also has one for
the Seeker missile.

01:14:12.152 --> 01:14:14.255 position:10% line:89% align:start
What else do you have to do?

01:14:14.288 --> 01:14:16.390 position:13% line:83% align:start
I still have to do a little
bit of wiring.

01:14:16.423 --> 01:14:18.192 position:19% line:83% align:start
On the superconducting
motor, I think.

01:14:19.426 --> 01:14:22.062 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Five more hours until
war declaration.

01:14:22.096 --> 01:14:24.865 position:13% line:77% align:start
Flying is going to take you
right into the middle of
the fighting.

01:14:24.898 --> 01:14:28.135 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'll do the software so
you can finish up the wiring.

01:14:28.168 --> 01:14:29.470 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah.

01:14:29.503 --> 01:14:32.273 position:13% line:83% align:start
Takuya, what's up with that
error message?!

01:14:32.306 --> 01:14:33.474 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] What?

01:14:33.507 --> 01:14:35.109 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] The one with
the Version Check.

01:14:35.142 --> 01:14:37.411 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Version Check?

01:14:37.444 --> 01:14:41.115 position:13% line:83% align:start
Oh, isn't that the part you
put together three years ago?

01:14:41.148 --> 01:14:43.350 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Oh, really?

01:14:43.384 --> 01:14:45.152 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] You haven't changed...

01:14:45.185 --> 01:14:46.453 position:41% line:89% align:start
Idiot.

01:15:10.210 --> 01:15:11.912 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Hiroki!
Take a look at this.

01:15:12.413 --> 01:15:13.981 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] What?

01:15:14.014 --> 01:15:15.416 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] The forecast of
the battle conditions

01:15:15.449 --> 01:15:17.217 position:5% line:89% align:start
off the coast of Tsugaru is out.

01:15:20.020 --> 01:15:21.255 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's just what we thought.

01:15:24.558 --> 01:15:27.428 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, the frontline will be
around the 42nd latitude.

01:15:27.461 --> 01:15:28.395 position:27% line:89% align:start
The inland area,

01:15:28.429 --> 01:15:31.265 position:13% line:83% align:start
especially around the Tower
is almost empty.

01:15:31.298 --> 01:15:33.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
The erosion of land is
pretty advanced.

01:15:33.467 --> 01:15:34.601 position:44% line:89% align:start
Well?

01:15:34.635 --> 01:15:36.570 position:10% line:83% align:start
We slip through by flying in
low with the jet engine...

01:15:37.938 --> 01:15:39.440 position:7% line:89% align:start
until we go through the strait.

01:15:39.473 --> 01:15:41.208 position:5% line:89% align:start
After passing the 42nd latitude,

01:15:41.241 --> 01:15:43.277 position:7% line:89% align:start
when we increase the altitude.

01:15:43.310 --> 01:15:45.112 position:27% line:89% align:start
How's that sound?

01:15:45.145 --> 01:15:49.950 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah... seems that's the
only way.

01:15:49.983 --> 01:15:51.318 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Takuya]
When you get to the Tower,

01:15:51.352 --> 01:15:54.054 position:13% line:83% align:start
coinciding with when Sayuri
wakes up,

01:15:54.088 --> 01:15:55.889 position:7% line:83% align:start
the disparate matter conversion
on the ground

01:15:55.923 --> 01:15:57.124 position:24% line:89% align:start
should start again.

01:15:57.157 --> 01:16:00.227 position:24% line:83% align:start
When that happens,
break away immediately.

01:16:00.260 --> 01:16:02.496 position:5% line:83% align:start
Once you're more than 10 km away
from the Tower,

01:16:02.529 --> 01:16:04.231 position:16% line:89% align:start
fire the Seeker missile.

01:16:04.264 --> 01:16:06.500 position:19% line:83% align:start
I programmed it to take
over from there.

01:16:06.533 --> 01:16:09.136 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Yeah. It should
be okay, right?

01:16:09.169 --> 01:16:12.272 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yeah. Two hours left until
the start of the war.

01:16:13.374 --> 01:16:15.042 position:19% line:83% align:start
We finished it earlier
than we thought.

01:16:15.075 --> 01:16:16.210 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mmhmm.

01:16:18.112 --> 01:16:19.213 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takuya] Hiroki...

01:16:19.246 --> 01:16:20.647 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Huh?

01:16:20.681 --> 01:16:23.884 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Is it possible that
you could play the violin?

01:16:27.421 --> 01:16:29.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] You know, you're
awfully single-minded.

01:16:29.423 --> 01:16:32.292 position:19% line:83% align:start
Kind of like an idiot,
aren't you?

01:16:32.326 --> 01:16:34.328 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's none of you business,
you jerk!

01:16:34.361 --> 01:16:36.096 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're the one who asked
me to play!

01:16:37.264 --> 01:16:38.665 position:19% line:89% align:start
Look this way, please.

01:16:38.699 --> 01:16:40.167 position:19% line:89% align:start
Just shut up, will ya?!

01:16:40.968 --> 01:16:42.403 position:21% line:89% align:start
Be quiet and listen!

01:17:26.480 --> 01:17:28.449 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>I can tell</i>
 <i>my body's trembling</i>

01:17:28.482 --> 01:17:30.617 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>at the premonition</i>
 <i>of waking u</i> p.

01:17:32.219 --> 01:17:36.990 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I don't know why, but the fear</i>
 <i>is strong than the hope I have.</i>

01:17:39.293 --> 01:17:42.329 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Hiroki]
 <i>"I always have a premonition</i>
 <i>of losing something."</i>

01:17:42.362 --> 01:17:44.531 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's what she said.</i>

01:17:44.565 --> 01:17:47.234 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I also feel the same premonition</i>
 <i>right now.</i>

01:17:50.404 --> 01:17:51.672 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>But...</i>

01:17:51.705 --> 01:17:54.541 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>As promised after school</i>
 <i>one day...</i>

01:17:54.575 --> 01:17:56.477 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm going to that Tower.</i>

01:18:00.147 --> 01:18:02.483 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Arisaka] The Tower's operating
levels are rising again!

01:18:02.516 --> 01:18:05.619 position:13% line:83% align:start
Erosion area of the branch
universes is expanding!

01:18:05.652 --> 01:18:08.422 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Its radius is
currently about 36km...

01:18:08.455 --> 01:18:10.057 position:24% line:83% align:start
in the middle of a
slow expansion.

01:18:11.225 --> 01:18:13.527 position:21% line:83% align:start
Is it reacting to the
sign of her waking up?

01:18:15.062 --> 01:18:17.364 position:5% line:89% align:start
You're sure it's okay, Oka-chan?

01:18:17.798 --> 01:18:19.233 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Maki] Professor!

01:18:19.266 --> 01:18:21.268 position:10% line:83% align:start
Sir, a declaration of war has
just been made!

01:18:23.070 --> 01:18:25.339 position:13% line:83% align:start
The first encounter is the
Tsugaru coast.

01:19:51.224 --> 01:19:53.260 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunfire]

01:20:39.807 --> 01:20:40.808 position:38% line:89% align:start
The land!

01:22:09.362 --> 01:22:11.999 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey, Sayuri.

01:22:12.033 --> 01:22:13.868 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] It's the
promised place.

01:22:15.736 --> 01:22:17.671 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>Those wings...</i>

01:22:17.704 --> 01:22:18.873 position:27% line:89% align:start
The <i>Bella Ciela.</i>

01:22:22.342 --> 01:22:24.244 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Sayuri] <i>My</i>
 <i>dream's disappearing.</i>

01:22:30.484 --> 01:22:31.919 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Oh, I see.</i>

01:22:33.320 --> 01:22:35.522 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I know now what</i>
 <i>I'm going to lose.</i>

01:22:36.490 --> 01:22:38.025 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Oh God...</i>

01:22:38.059 --> 01:22:40.494 position:30% line:89% align:start
Please, God...

01:22:40.527 --> 01:22:41.996 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri and Hiroki] Please, God.

01:22:42.029 --> 01:22:44.431 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Please wake Sayuri
from her sleep.

01:22:44.464 --> 01:22:48.468 position:30% line:89% align:start
Please. Please.

01:22:48.502 --> 01:22:53.440 position:38% line:77% align:start
[Sayuri]
Please, even if it's just for
a moment after waking up,

01:22:53.473 --> 01:22:55.943 position:7% line:83% align:start
please don't erase the feeling
that I have right now.

01:22:59.046 --> 01:23:00.447 position:19% line:89% align:start
I have to tell Hiroki,

01:23:00.480 --> 01:23:04.919 position:13% line:77% align:start
how special the connection
between our hearts was
in my dream and...

01:23:04.952 --> 01:23:07.521 position:19% line:83% align:start
how much I was longing
for Hiroki

01:23:07.554 --> 01:23:10.724 position:30% line:83% align:start
and how deeply
he longed for me...

01:23:10.757 --> 01:23:13.961 position:13% line:83% align:start
in a world where there was
no one around.

01:23:15.428 --> 01:23:16.964 position:38% line:89% align:start
Sayuri...

01:23:18.365 --> 01:23:19.566 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] Please.

01:23:19.599 --> 01:23:23.004 position:13% line:83% align:start
I have to tell him how much
I've loved him all this time.

01:23:23.037 --> 01:23:24.906 position:16% line:83% align:start
If I could... If I could
tell him that much,

01:23:24.939 --> 01:23:27.374 position:13% line:89% align:start
I don't need anything else.

01:23:27.407 --> 01:23:30.677 position:21% line:83% align:start
Please, even for just
a second...

01:23:30.710 --> 01:23:32.546 position:16% line:89% align:start
this feeling that I have!

01:23:34.447 --> 01:23:35.482 position:41% line:89% align:start
Please!

01:23:59.439 --> 01:24:00.607 position:38% line:89% align:start
Sayuri...

01:24:06.113 --> 01:24:07.347 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hiroki.

01:24:11.618 --> 01:24:14.454 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Maki] Disparate matter
conversion is rapidly expanding!

01:24:14.487 --> 01:24:15.990 position:16% line:89% align:start
Ezo's being swallowed in!

01:24:35.142 --> 01:24:36.509 position:38% line:89% align:start
Sayuri...

01:24:41.514 --> 01:24:42.850 position:38% line:89% align:start
I have...

01:24:45.086 --> 01:24:48.755 position:10% line:83% align:start
I have to tell you something
very important.

01:24:48.788 --> 01:24:50.057 position:27% line:89% align:start
But it's gone...

01:24:52.126 --> 01:24:53.526 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Sayuri] It's gone!

01:25:06.173 --> 01:25:07.842 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] Everything will
be all right.

01:25:07.875 --> 01:25:09.676 position:16% line:89% align:start
Because you're awake now.

01:25:10.677 --> 01:25:12.646 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're back now. Back.

01:25:19.253 --> 01:25:21.554 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hiroki] Welcome back, Sayuri.

01:26:44.905 --> 01:26:47.640 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hiroki] <i>We've lost our</i>
 <i>promised place in this world.</i>

01:26:48.608 --> 01:26:50.044 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>But even so,</i>

01:26:50.077 --> 01:26:52.046 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>we'll start living now.</i>

